{"term":"1967","caseName":"Protective Committee for Independent Stockholders of TMT Trailer Ferry, Inc. v. Anderson","caseLink":"https://www.oyez.org/cases/1967/38","caseTranscripts":[{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - November 08, 1967","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren15/oral_argument_audio/14859","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Protective Committee for Independent Stockholders of TMT Trailer Ferry Incorporated, Petitioner versus C.Gordon Anderson, Trustee.","start":0,"stop":13.803,"duration":13.8},{"text":"Mr. Simmons, you may continue your argument.","start":13.803,"stop":20.952,"duration":7.15}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, may it please the Court.","start":20.952,"stop":24.928,"duration":3.98},{"text":"I would -- the issued that I will discuss first this morning is the issue concerning the employment of the trustee by the reorganized company.","start":24.928,"stop":36.9,"duration":11.97},{"text":"The success of the trustee in operating the business of a data is best illustrated by the fact that when he took over in November of 1959 -- 1957, almost exactly 10 years ago, business was at a stand still.","start":36.9,"stop":60.704,"duration":23.8},{"text":"The ships were not moving.","start":60.704,"stop":63.055,"duration":2.35},{"text":"They were in bad need of repair and there was little hope for the business so everyone thought.","start":63.055,"stop":71.105,"duration":8.05},{"text":"Under his able management, the business grew to the point where by 1964, the end of the -- or 1965, when we began by the end of 1965, when we began to consummate the present plan of reorganization, the business was able to pay off in cash over $1,500,000 in claims being all of the preferred claims and all of the secured claims.","start":71.105,"stop":113.28,"duration":42.18},{"text":"Of this sum, about $1,100,000 went to the United States Government for its tax and nontax claims.","start":113.28,"stop":123.948,"duration":10.67},{"text":"And of -- and $250,000 went to the -- to pay off the Caplan mortgage, the compromise of the Caplan mortgage claim.","start":123.948,"stop":135.433,"duration":11.49},{"text":"This -- the payment of this large sum of money to pay off all of these claimants in these two categories, did not come out of the earnings of the business.","start":135.433,"stop":146.009,"duration":10.58},{"text":"Most of it came from a loan of $1,250,000 that the reorganized company was permitted by the Court to make from a bank in Florida, a long-term loan which reorg --","start":146.009,"stop":161.253,"duration":15.24}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"How much came out of the earnings?","start":161.253,"stop":163.269,"duration":2.02}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The rest of it came out of the earnings.","start":163.269,"stop":164.519,"duration":1.25}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"What was the rest of it?","start":164.519,"stop":166.776,"duration":2.26},{"text":"Who said --","start":166.776,"stop":167.308,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The total of the claims was -- in excess of $1,500,000, so of that sum approximately between $250,000 and $300,000 came out of the earnings of the data.","start":167.308,"stop":182.452,"duration":15.14}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"In the 10 years.","start":182.452,"stop":184.085,"duration":1.63},{"text":"In the --","start":184.085,"stop":184.187,"duration":0.1}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes Your Honor.","start":184.187,"stop":184.394,"duration":0.21}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- ten years?","start":184.394,"stop":185.475,"duration":1.08}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The earnings had been a great deal more than that.","start":185.475,"stop":187.984,"duration":2.51},{"text":"Most of the earnings had been plowed back in to the business to purchase new or purchase more LST's.","start":187.984,"stop":196.427,"duration":8.44},{"text":"When the trustees took over, they were operating only three of these old World War II LST's.","start":196.427,"stop":203.454,"duration":7.03},{"text":"During his tenure, they have purchased and converted two more of the LST's so they're operating five.","start":203.454,"stop":211.828,"duration":8.37},{"text":"And most of the earnings of the business during that period of time had to be plowed back into additional assets.","start":211.828,"stop":220.08,"duration":8.25},{"text":"So it was inevitable, almost inevitable that persons who were interested in inquiring this company upon reorganization would want to retain the services of -- the good services of this trustee, and so it was has it been emphasized in all of the briefs.","start":220.08,"stop":241.914,"duration":21.83},{"text":"All of the plans of reorganization have contemplated the retention of the services of this trustee.","start":241.914,"stop":251.302,"duration":9.39},{"text":"The present plan of reorganization, this internal plan which I have described to the Court, was prepared by the committee appointed by the District Judge to represent the unsecured creditors as a class.","start":251.302,"stop":271.477,"duration":20.17},{"text":"This committee -- the larger creditors of course were represented by their own counsel.","start":271.477,"stop":277.349,"duration":5.87},{"text":"And so the Court appended a committee of two experienced local attorneys to represent the general mass of the unsecured creditors.","start":277.349,"stop":287.626,"duration":10.28},{"text":"And this committee presented and suggested this internal plan of reorganization which included the two compromises of the claims that are among the issues here and also included a provision which contemplated the retention of the trustee's management by the reorganized company.","start":287.626,"stop":307.362,"duration":19.74},{"text":"It did not require the retention of that management.","start":307.362,"stop":311.431,"duration":4.07},{"text":"It merely permitted it and put everyone on notice that though -- the proponents of the plan contemplated the possible retention of the trustee and his good management team.","start":311.431,"stop":325.631,"duration":14.2},{"text":"Now, our first point of course is that Chapter X of the Bankruptcy Act does not preclude the employment of the trustee and all of the recorded cases thus far, that have touched on this subject have permitted the employment of the trustee.","start":325.631,"stop":344.783,"duration":19.15},{"text":"Or rather more accurately stated, cases as cited in the brief of the Securities and Exchange Commission, they have cited to the Court instances where the trustee has been retained or employed by a reorganized company.","start":344.783,"stop":360.422,"duration":15.64},{"text":"And there is no -- there are no decisions where that has been prohibited as a matter of law.","start":360.422,"stop":366.334,"duration":5.91},{"text":"It appears to us that the matter is left entirely to the discretion of the District Court under Section 221 (5) of the Bankruptcy Act, which simply requires a complete disclosure of the identity, qualifications and affiliations of the persons who are to be the initial directors and officers of the reorganized company and the finding that their appointment by the Court would be compatible with the interest of the data and consistent with public policy.","start":366.334,"stop":397.566,"duration":31.23},{"text":"We think this is a finding of fact to be made in each case.","start":397.566,"stop":401.172,"duration":3.61},{"text":"It has been made in this case by the District Judge that this trustee's retention would be in the best interest of the data.","start":401.172,"stop":410.436,"duration":9.26},{"text":"The opposing contention is based upon an interpretation of Sections 156 and 158 of the Bankruptcy Act, which pertain to the appointment of a disinterested trustee.","start":410.436,"stop":427.956,"duration":17.52},{"text":"But nothing in those statutes asses or implies that an interest in employment by the reorganized company is a disqualification to act as trustee.","start":427.956,"stop":439.129,"duration":11.17},{"text":"Opposing counsel would write into the statute a meaning that is not stated.","start":439.129,"stop":444.67,"duration":5.54},{"text":"Their position is not sound and presupposes that a trustee will necessarily breach his trust if he contemplates continuation of his employment.","start":444.67,"stop":457.471,"duration":12.8},{"text":"This is contrary to human experience or a person with an incentive will do a better job than one who knows that his services will be terminated no matter how well he performs.","start":457.471,"stop":474.957,"duration":17.49},{"text":"Opposing argument of opposing counsel of course overlooks the benefits to the data of being able to retain the services of a good and successful trustee.","start":474.957,"stop":484.415,"duration":9.46},{"text":"It also overlooks the fact that all of the trustee's actions are subject to court approval.","start":484.415,"stop":493.826,"duration":9.41},{"text":"The criticism that you have heard here yesterday expressed of this trustee and the things that he did involve matters that were all approved by the Court.","start":493.826,"stop":505.713,"duration":11.89},{"text":"For example, the towing contract, the award of a towing contract was criticized and the recommendation of the compromise of these two large claims was criticized.","start":505.713,"stop":519.799,"duration":14.09},{"text":"But both of those matters have been the subject of many hearings in court and an opportunity to be heard by all parties and throughout this proceeding.","start":519.799,"stop":532.027,"duration":12.23},{"text":"That has been true with respect to all actions of the trustee.","start":532.027,"stop":535.661,"duration":3.63},{"text":"They have been subjected to a great deal of scrutiny, a great deal of criticism by the Stockholders Committee.","start":535.661,"stop":541.598,"duration":5.94}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"Does the record show the background to this trustee and (Inaudible)?","start":541.598,"stop":547.916,"duration":6.32}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":547.916,"stop":549.274,"duration":1.36},{"text":"The trustee is a retired successful merchant.","start":549.274,"stop":556.185,"duration":6.91},{"text":"For many years, he was a manager of a large retail department store and a successful reputable businessman in Miami.","start":556.185,"stop":566.83,"duration":10.65},{"text":"He'd lived in Miami for many years.","start":566.83,"stop":568.524,"duration":1.69},{"text":"He'd been associated with large department stores.","start":568.524,"stop":570.784,"duration":2.26},{"text":"This is well-known in the community.","start":570.784,"stop":573.011,"duration":2.23},{"text":"He'd retired and the Court appointed him as trustee.","start":573.011,"stop":577.311,"duration":4.3},{"text":"He'd had no interest or knowledge of TMT at all before that.","start":577.311,"stop":581.876,"duration":4.56},{"text":"He'd been in the -- he's just a good businessman and he brought to the trusteeship with him the man that had been his general manager and right-hand man in the retail merchandizing business, Mr. (Inaudible), who brought a great deal of know-how and sound business methods to this trusteeship.","start":581.876,"stop":604.423,"duration":22.55},{"text":"It would appear that opposing counsel would write into the Bankruptcy Act something that Congress has not written into it.","start":604.423,"stop":616.625,"duration":12.2},{"text":"And I think it was admitted yesterday that in 1948 or 1958, the SEC sponsored enacting Congress that would have expressly prohibited the employment of a trustee for a period of two years after the conclusion of reorganization proceedings and it would appear that the SEC knows that Congress has not yet prohibited the employment of the trustee.","start":616.625,"stop":646.408,"duration":29.78},{"text":"So we say that the Fifth Circuit placed a proper construction on the statutes involved here when it held that the proponents of the plan that that -- what the -- the dis -- the appellate court held that the trustee is not disinterested unless the proponents of the plan assured him of emoluments and security rather than merely nominating him for approval by the Court and subject to the usual control of the board of directors.","start":646.408,"stop":679.322,"duration":32.91},{"text":"Now, one of the most imp -- significant factors in this whole issue is that, no attempt has been made to disqualify this trustee because of his interest in employment by the reorganized company or for any other reason.","start":679.322,"stop":700.487,"duration":21.16},{"text":"If the position of opposing counsel is correct, this trustee has been disqualified since early 1959 for that was the first time when a plan of reorganization was proposed that contemplated his employment.","start":700.487,"stop":721.213,"duration":20.73},{"text":"Every plan has contemplated his employment since early 1959.","start":721.213,"stop":728.984,"duration":7.77},{"text":"So we say to the Court that it is too late now to urge that his past disqualification prohibits him from being employed in the future.","start":728.984,"stop":744.126,"duration":15.14},{"text":"The plan has been substantially consummated.","start":744.126,"stop":748.564,"duration":4.44},{"text":"New directors have taken over the operations of the business and are running the company with this trustee in his team in charge of operations.","start":748.564,"stop":758.759,"duration":10.2},{"text":"It would be highly inequitable to re -- now require the reorganized company to fire him and force him -- enforce it to employ a less qualified person to run the business.","start":758.759,"stop":774.513,"duration":15.75},{"text":"We say that the petitioner and the Securities and Exchange Commission are now estopped to raise this question after having permitted the trustee for eight years to operate the business of this data, knowing all that time that he was being considered for employment by the reorganized company without coming in and specifically asking the Court to remove him for that reason.","start":774.513,"stop":806.597,"duration":32.08},{"text":"Another point that I want to emphasize is, that this issue was decided by the Fifth Circuit in its 1964 decision when this plan of reorganization was first reviewed by that Court.","start":806.597,"stop":824.512,"duration":17.91},{"text":"You recall it has been reviewed twice and we're here after the second review.","start":824.512,"stop":833.058,"duration":8.55},{"text":"The very provisions of the plan that are here now were before the Fifth Circuit in 1964 and the Fifth Circuit upheld those provisions in the plan with respect to the employment of the trustee.","start":833.058,"stop":848.183,"duration":15.13},{"text":"Therefore, that decision became the law of the case for no appeal was taken from it.","start":848.183,"stop":857.622,"duration":9.44},{"text":"And we say that this Court should now recognize under the circumstances of this case, the law of the case on the question of the trustee's employment as it was decided by the Fifth Circuit in 1964.","start":857.622,"stop":874.179,"duration":16.56},{"text":"When the Fifth Circuit sent the plan back in 1964, it sent it back only to determine its feasibility in the light of the companion decision which it made in another case requiring payment in full of the Government nontax claims.","start":874.179,"stop":896.867,"duration":22.69},{"text":"These claims amounted to $900,000 so there was a question as to whether the data would be able to do it.","start":896.867,"stop":903.188,"duration":6.32},{"text":"But by means of this bank loan that I referred to a while ago, the $1,250,000 borrowed in that amount of money, the data was able to pay the Government nontax claims in full as well, as I have said, all other preferred and secured claims.","start":903.188,"stop":920.028,"duration":16.84},{"text":"So the plan of reorganization that we now have before us, the amended plan is amended only in one particular, one material particular: that is to provide for the payment of the nontax claims of the Government in full.","start":920.028,"stop":935.153,"duration":15.13},{"text":"It was not amended in any particular with respect to the employment of the trustee.","start":935.153,"stop":941.212,"duration":6.06},{"text":"And the amended plan that we have here now approves the appointment of the same officers and directors of the reorganized company as the first plan did back in 1964 when it first went to the appellate court.","start":941.212,"stop":961.609,"duration":20.4},{"text":"Now the Court well knows that the law of the case is a salutary one designed to end litigation.","start":961.609,"stop":969.339,"duration":7.73},{"text":"And under the decisions of this and other courts, it should be recognized and followed, unless there are impelling reasons for reversing the former decision.","start":969.339,"stop":981.703,"duration":12.36},{"text":"On the contrary in this case, there are impelling reasons for allowing it to stand.","start":981.703,"stop":988.373,"duration":6.67},{"text":"Number one, there's been no effort to remove the trustee, as I have pointed out.","start":988.373,"stop":994.449,"duration":6.08},{"text":"Number two, the creditors, who are the real parties in interest here, want to retain the trustee.","start":994.449,"stop":1001.346,"duration":6.9},{"text":"Not a single creditor, not one, has come forward to object to the employment of the trustee by the reorganized company.","start":1001.346,"stop":1010.891,"duration":9.54},{"text":"These creditors of course are now the new stockholders, the new owners of the reorganized company.","start":1010.891,"stop":1017.381,"duration":6.49},{"text":"On the contrary, they have urged to the District Court the approval of his appointment or his being a director and the president of the reorganized company.","start":1017.381,"stop":1029.849,"duration":12.47},{"text":"Third, substantial consummation of this plan has taken place as I have previously described to this Court.","start":1029.849,"stop":1039.51,"duration":9.66},{"text":"And it would certainly serve no useful purpose in this case to prohibit his future employment because of a -- an alleged statutory pass disqualification to serve his trustee.","start":1039.51,"stop":1054.07,"duration":14.56},{"text":"And finally, it is apparent from the record in this case as the District Court so found that the best interest of the reorganized company require to re -- they require the retention of the valuable services of the trustee and his management team.","start":1054.07,"stop":1072.976,"duration":18.91},{"text":"I would like to -- unless the Court has some questions on that point, I would like to go to the next point.","start":1072.976,"stop":1081.419,"duration":8.44}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I'd like to ask this Mr. Simmons --","start":1081.419,"stop":1083.582,"duration":2.16}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1083.582,"stop":1084.696,"duration":1.11}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- were these alleged conflicts of interest raised in the court below, in the District Court?","start":1084.696,"stop":1092.573,"duration":7.88}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Asserted time and time again in pleadings --","start":1092.573,"stop":1095.294,"duration":2.72}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"But the District Court make specific findings as to his lack of it?","start":1095.294,"stop":1105.693,"duration":10.4}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No Your Honor.","start":1105.693,"stop":1106.84,"duration":1.15},{"text":"I'd have to put it this way.","start":1106.84,"stop":1108.632,"duration":1.79},{"text":"At no point did -- has anybody raised any of these things as it faces for disqualifying the trustee as trustee.","start":1108.632,"stop":1119.961,"duration":11.33},{"text":"They keep raising them in this litigation through the years as a reason why he should not be retained or employed by the reorganized company.","start":1119.961,"stop":1133.122,"duration":13.16},{"text":"But not as a re -- this is what's inconsistent about the whole thing.","start":1133.122,"stop":1137.795,"duration":4.67},{"text":"At no point have they said, and I think counsel for the SEC admitted that in response to a question yesterday that they had not raised the question about his qualifications as trustee.","start":1137.795,"stop":1151.146,"duration":13.35},{"text":"They say just as a matter of prophylactic rule they say, that he shouldn't be retained by the reorganized company.","start":1151.146,"stop":1159.67,"duration":8.52}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, was evidenced -- evidence was introduced as to that conflict of interest alleged?","start":1159.67,"stop":1169.171,"duration":9.5}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No, because there was never any issue presented to the Court on it.","start":1169.171,"stop":1172.725,"duration":3.55},{"text":"It was asserted from time to time.","start":1172.725,"stop":1174.714,"duration":1.99},{"text":"It was asserted that the trustee for example, for some reason favored the towing company that he recommended that the towing contract was awarded to that that the fact that he awarded the -- recommended the award of the contract without competitive bidding or something like that, indicated that he favored that company as against maybe somebody else.","start":1174.714,"stop":1200.296,"duration":25.58},{"text":"And these things were asserted but -- well that particular issue was heard in connection with the towing contract and overruled.","start":1200.296,"stop":1207.176,"duration":6.88},{"text":"The Court approved the award of the towing contract to the company recommended by the trustee.","start":1207.176,"stop":1213.26,"duration":6.08},{"text":"That's the way these things came up.","start":1213.26,"stop":1215.691,"duration":2.43},{"text":"On individual issues and actions of the trustee, they would object to him and the Court would enter an order.","start":1215.691,"stop":1222.071,"duration":6.38},{"text":"And in no time was a clear cut issue presented to the Court that the trustee was disqualified.","start":1222.071,"stop":1233.242,"duration":11.17},{"text":"The next issue is the -- that I will discuss is the matter of the compromise of the lien claims against the vessels of the data.","start":1233.242,"stop":1246.445,"duration":13.2},{"text":"Now, when this plan came back from the appellate court in 1964 and the appellate court had held that that this $900,000, a nontax claim to the Government had to be paid in full in cash.","start":1246.445,"stop":1263.624,"duration":17.18},{"text":"It posed a real practical problem.","start":1263.624,"stop":1267.935,"duration":4.31},{"text":"In addition -- because in addition to this $1 million -- actually $1 million one -- $1,200,000 in tax and preferred claims that had to be paid in cash.","start":1267.935,"stop":1284.439,"duration":16.5},{"text":"There were these lien claims against the vessels of the data.","start":1284.439,"stop":1289.903,"duration":5.46},{"text":"I'm adding to approximately a million dollars.","start":1289.903,"stop":1293.884,"duration":3.98},{"text":"Well something had to give or it would not be able to work out a plan of reorganization.","start":1293.884,"stop":1300.586,"duration":6.7},{"text":"So, it was inevitable that settlement discussion would take place with respect to these lien claims against the vessels of the data.","start":1300.586,"stop":1309.309,"duration":8.72},{"text":"The two largest lien claims were the ones in controversy here.","start":1309.309,"stop":1317.533,"duration":8.22},{"text":"The Caplan mortgage was in the principal sum of $330,000 and it was a preferred ship mortgage on all the vessels of the data.","start":1317.533,"stop":1332.052,"duration":14.52},{"text":"The other lien claim was the $574,000 lien -- series of lien claims again -- by Merrill-Stevens against all of the vessels of the data.","start":1332.052,"stop":1344.772,"duration":12.72},{"text":"So with the approval of the Court and the knowledge of everyone concerned, settlement discussions took place between the trustee, the trustee's counsel and counsel for these creditors.","start":1344.772,"stop":1358.104,"duration":13.33},{"text":"And the result was that when this creditors committee proposed the present internal plan of reorganization, that plan included in it as an integral part the proposed compromises of these two claims.","start":1358.104,"stop":1376.298,"duration":18.19},{"text":"The Caplan mortgage claim of base amount of $330,000, which had added to it interest, cost and attorney's fees which would have make it at least $500,000, was reduced to $250,000 payable in cash.","start":1376.298,"stop":1395.439,"duration":19.14},{"text":"And that -- and in connection with the consummation of the plan that has taken place, that $250,000 has been paid to the Caplan mortgage trustees.","start":1395.439,"stop":1410.34,"duration":14.9},{"text":"The only other fact in that compromise was that the interest due -- accrued interest due on that mortgage was paid against common stock of the reorganized company or satisfied by giving them common stock.","start":1410.34,"stop":1425.773,"duration":15.43},{"text":"Now, the Merrill-Stevens claim, lien claims against the vessel amounted to $574,000 and the compromised with Merrill-Stevens provided that those claims would be taken off of the vessels entirely and that amount would become an unsecured claim payable in common stock of the reorganized company.","start":1425.773,"stop":1447.434,"duration":21.66},{"text":"And that was the settlement there.","start":1447.434,"stop":1449.821,"duration":2.39},{"text":"The result of these two compromises meant that the plan was feasible; that instead of having to pay up perhaps puts to a million dollars or satisfied puts to a million dollars in lien claims of preferred ship mortgage claims against the vessels of the data.","start":1449.821,"stop":1468.365,"duration":18.54},{"text":"The data would only have to pay $250,000 and the balance in the common stock of the reorganized company which it didn't cost him anything in cash.","start":1468.365,"stop":1477.759,"duration":9.39},{"text":"And as a result of these compromises, the plan was made feasible.","start":1477.759,"stop":1485.246,"duration":7.49},{"text":"Now, the objections to the compromises are, the SEC states in its brief that the record contains insufficient facts for the Court to form, to make an informed judgment of -- on the merits of the compromise.","start":1485.246,"stop":1505.781,"duration":20.53},{"text":"The petitioner, the Stockholders Committee, in addition says there was inadequate investigation of the objections to these two claims.","start":1505.781,"stop":1517.643,"duration":11.86},{"text":"Now neither of these contentions is sustained by the record.","start":1517.643,"stop":1522.322,"duration":4.68},{"text":"I'm not going to discuss the Caplan mortgage claim and the terrific investigation that was made of it.","start":1522.322,"stop":1528.755,"duration":6.43},{"text":"It's stated in our brief and Mr. Spitzer represents the Caplan mortgage people and will go into the details of that during his time before the Court when I finish.","start":1528.755,"stop":1539.257,"duration":10.5},{"text":"But, with respect to the Merrill-Stevens claim, we've outlined in our brief the numerous pleadings and places in the record where the facts concerning this claim and particularly the objections to it are set forth in great detail particularly by opposing counsel.","start":1539.257,"stop":1559.239,"duration":19.98},{"text":"And insofar as investigation is concerned, the record shows as we point out in our brief that no less than four investigations were made of the Merrill-Stevens claim.","start":1559.239,"stop":1571.778,"duration":12.54},{"text":"There is a reference in the record to a trustee's investigation in 1959 which he reported in his opinion, the amount of the claim and so far the value of Merrill-Stevens services was concerned was substantially awarded or justified.","start":1571.778,"stop":1590.43,"duration":18.65},{"text":"Admittedly, that wasn't much of an investigation.","start":1590.43,"stop":1593.246,"duration":2.82},{"text":"We don't have much in the record on it.","start":1593.246,"stop":1597.083,"duration":3.84},{"text":"The next investigation was the Securities and Exchange Commission investigation in 1961, and they reported that rather thoroughly to the Court and to -- in his own record.","start":1597.083,"stop":1609.676,"duration":12.59},{"text":"The Stockholders Committee made --","start":1609.676,"stop":1611.564,"duration":1.89}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"What was the result -- what did they report?","start":1611.564,"stop":1614.509,"duration":2.94}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"They recommended -- they reported that their investigation -- they had very little criticism of the amount of the claim.","start":1614.509,"stop":1627.064,"duration":12.56},{"text":"Bear in mind that the total amount of the claim was $1,600,000 and there is little objection to the fact that Merrill-Stevens did perform extensive work on the vessel and for which it was not paid.","start":1627.064,"stop":1641.475,"duration":14.41},{"text":"And there's little dispute as to the amount of the claim.","start":1641.475,"stop":1645.271,"duration":3.8},{"text":"But the SEC objections stated that Merrill-Stevens did not -- the main objections are -- with respect to the million dollar claim against the Carib Queen for rebuilding the Carib Queen, Merrill-Stevens did not properly convert the vessel.","start":1645.271,"stop":1663.384,"duration":18.11},{"text":"They did not comply with the terms of the contract.","start":1663.384,"stop":1666.818,"duration":3.43},{"text":"They did not properly repair the vessel and they fail to establish the value of its work and materials.","start":1666.818,"stop":1677.666,"duration":10.85},{"text":"And in addition, the petitioner in its charges against -- objections to the Merrill-Stevens claim, repeated what the SEC had said and went on to say to charge that Merrill-Stevens is liable in thought for negligence in performing the work on the vessel causing in part the downfall of TMT.","start":1677.666,"stop":1704.608,"duration":26.94},{"text":"They also charged that Merrill-Stevens bought stock in TMT for which it has not been paid.","start":1704.608,"stop":1712.781,"duration":8.17},{"text":"And that is a substance of the charges that they made against Merrill-Stevens.","start":1712.781,"stop":1720.444,"duration":7.66},{"text":"Merrill-Stevens filed pleadings denying all of these.","start":1720.444,"stop":1725.29,"duration":4.85},{"text":"And in addition to the Securities and Exchange Commission investigation and the Stockholders Committee investigation, the trustee or rather -- our firm, as counsel for the trustee, took all of these information that was made available to us by the SEC and the Stockholders Committee and by Merrill-Stevens and made an off-the-record investigation of all of these things just as attorneys always do in connect -- when the question of settlement of a claim is being considered.","start":1725.29,"stop":1765.141,"duration":39.85},{"text":"We studied all of these and reported to the Court that -- as follows, two attorneys in the office of counsel for the trustee have examined the factual data, gathered in the trustee's investigation of the objections to the Merrill-Stevens claim.","start":1765.141,"stop":1784.118,"duration":18.98},{"text":"And it is the considered opinion of both attorneys that the possibility is remote of obtaining any reduction or material reduction in the amount of the Merrill-Stevens claim by litigating the objections against it.","start":1784.118,"stop":1797.426,"duration":13.31},{"text":"Trial of the issues raised by the objections would be time consuming and would result in unnecessary delay in formulating a plan of reorganization.","start":1797.426,"stop":1808.824,"duration":11.4},{"text":"That is our considered judgment of this compromise as attorneys for the trustee.","start":1808.824,"stop":1816.207,"duration":7.38},{"text":"And I say to the Court and all candidates, one thing to sit up in your office and prepare pleadings and make objections and file fraud charges.","start":1816.207,"stop":1825.353,"duration":9.15},{"text":"But it's quite another thing when you're on the firing line and have to make the decision as to whether you're going to file a lawsuit by the claim or compromise it on a reasonable basis.","start":1825.353,"stop":1836.923,"duration":11.57},{"text":"And we advise the trustee and we advise the Court that this compromise should be accepted and the Court accepted our opinion.","start":1836.923,"stop":1846.572,"duration":9.65}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the Court --","start":1846.572,"stop":1846.74,"duration":0.17}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"And that's it.","start":1846.74,"stop":1847.576,"duration":0.84}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the Court have any hearing on the subject as to --","start":1847.576,"stop":1851.922,"duration":4.35}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The --","start":1851.922,"stop":1852.057,"duration":0.13}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- the relative merits of these reports that were made?","start":1852.057,"stop":1855.452,"duration":3.39}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Not expressly, the -- bear in mind that the proposed compromises were an integral part of the plan of reorganization.","start":1855.452,"stop":1866.637,"duration":11.18},{"text":"And therefore, the hearings -- the extensive hearings that were held on two different occasions in 1962 and in 1965 again, on the merits of the plan whether it should be approved or not, are the hearings that involved everything in connection with the plan, including these objections.","start":1866.637,"stop":1887.108,"duration":20.47},{"text":"And our report to the Court on this was -- came out in there.","start":1887.108,"stop":1890.391,"duration":3.28}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"What was your --","start":1890.391,"stop":1890.45,"duration":0.06}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, was there any -- was there any evidence taken on -- before the Court in any proceeding on these reports?","start":1890.45,"stop":1899.648,"duration":9.2}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No, we had -- no evidence was taken on it.","start":1899.648,"stop":1903.724,"duration":4.08},{"text":"We had in these investigation reports and -- in the record, sufficient facts to show on the one hand what the basis of Merrill-Stevens claim was and on the other hand, what the basis of the objections were and no evidence was taken.","start":1903.724,"stop":1920.452,"duration":16.73}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Was there any request made by either side to have it -- to have a hearing before the Court?","start":1920.452,"stop":1926.623,"duration":6.17}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The Stockholders Committee kept yelling for more investigation, more investigation.","start":1926.623,"stop":1933.159,"duration":6.54},{"text":"We did not think more investigation was necessary.","start":1933.159,"stop":1936.608,"duration":3.45}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Do they -- did they ask for a hearing before the Courts on the facts?","start":1936.608,"stop":1942.395,"duration":5.79}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"They may have.","start":1942.395,"stop":1944.481,"duration":2.09},{"text":"But in the meantime, none was necessary because the creditors committee had proposed the compromises and we'd recommended the approval of the compromises and we didn't think that any good would come of any hearings on the objection.","start":1944.481,"stop":1962.037,"duration":17.56},{"text":"We didn't think we had to get in and upheld the facts before the Court and try the thing -- before the Court to determine whether or not there should be an approval of the compromise.","start":1962.037,"stop":1971.588,"duration":9.55}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"What is the -- what do you think normally happens within a -- when an objection is filed to the claim?","start":1971.588,"stop":1979.598,"duration":8.01}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"This Court has held and the law seems to be clear that you don't have to hear objections to a claim, parti -- where the settlement of that claim is proposed as an integral part of the plan of reorganization.","start":1979.598,"stop":1999.018,"duration":19.42},{"text":"The hearings on the feasibility and the fairness and so forth of the plan that are held in -- are the hearings in which those matters are considered.","start":1999.018,"stop":2006.04,"duration":7.02}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, let's assume some creditor votes against the plan and has also filed an objection to somebody else's claim.","start":2006.04,"stop":2013.106,"duration":7.07},{"text":"Do you think that the vote of the two thirds of the class keeps him from having a hearing on the objection of that plan?","start":2013.106,"stop":2022.388,"duration":9.28}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No, sir, I do not.","start":2022.388,"stop":2023.642,"duration":1.25}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well how about this case then?","start":2023.642,"stop":2024.918,"duration":1.28},{"text":"How come the stockholders didn't get a hearing on their objection?","start":2024.918,"stop":2029.257,"duration":4.34}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"They --","start":2029.257,"stop":2029.297,"duration":0.04}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"The only reason you've got this is -- is the only answer that they had no interest in the reorganized -- reorganization?","start":2029.297,"stop":2034.495,"duration":5.2}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That's our principal answer.","start":2034.495,"stop":2035.69,"duration":1.2}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"If they did had an interest, would you say they've would've -- a hearing on the objections would've been required?","start":2035.69,"stop":2046.113,"duration":10.42}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Not where the compromises proposed as an integral part of the plan of reorganization and the hearings that you have on that are the -- the hearings on the plan go into the whole thing including the compromise, if you don't have any specific hearing on it.","start":2046.113,"stop":2064.041,"duration":17.93}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"What difference would that make if the compromise was in fact fraudulent?","start":2064.041,"stop":2071.574,"duration":7.53},{"text":"Why shouldn't they be in here of some kind to determine the liability of claim?","start":2071.574,"stop":2085.684,"duration":14.11}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, if there had been any basis for a charge of fraud in this case, I think we would have had a hearing.","start":2085.684,"stop":2093.976,"duration":8.29},{"text":"For one of the things we emphasize is that there's no facts in this record to show that Merrill-Stevens is guilty of any fraud.","start":2093.976,"stop":2105.399,"duration":11.42},{"text":"Now -- and we point that out in our brief.","start":2105.399,"stop":2108.159,"duration":2.76},{"text":"Counsel appeared yesterday, said that Merrill-Stevens was guilty of fraud and in the next breadth said the fraud was connected with Sha -- with Abrams and Shaffer who wrecked the company.","start":2108.159,"stop":2125.241,"duration":17.08},{"text":"There's not a thing in this record to connect Merrill-Stevens with Shaffer and Abrams or the Caplan mortgage people at all.","start":2125.241,"stop":2133.348,"duration":8.11},{"text":"That is prior to the beginning of the reorganization proceedings in this thing.","start":2133.348,"stop":2137.423,"duration":4.07},{"text":"There is no basis and this is the point that we make in our brief.","start":2137.423,"stop":2141.402,"duration":3.98},{"text":"There's no basis for fraud against -- the only charges against Merrill-Stevens are that they didn't repair the vessel properly and are responsible for it breaking down at sea and things of that kind.","start":2141.402,"stop":2152.167,"duration":10.76},{"text":"Things involving tort claims against that which when we waived these things, we decided that the burden of proof just wasn't worth going after, particularly when the creditors wanted it.","start":2152.167,"stop":2164.313,"duration":12.15}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Maybe you would've decided that representing the trustee, but as with the Court any interest in that whether it's fraud or whether it's tort, that reduces -- well let's say, reduces a claim of a million and a half down to a half a million.","start":2164.313,"stop":2180.414,"duration":16.1},{"text":"Wouldn't the Court have an interest in determining that fact when there are reports by the Stockholders and by the SEC to the effect that that is a fact?","start":2180.414,"stop":2192.144,"duration":11.73},{"text":"I would think that in the interest of preserving the assets of the company for anybody who might be entitled to it that the Court would be interested in determining that fact.","start":2192.144,"stop":2208.7,"duration":16.56}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, the Court was interested and so are we as counsel for the trustee.","start":2208.7,"stop":2212.812,"duration":4.11},{"text":"We're anxious to recover everything possible for the debtor in this particular case.","start":2212.812,"stop":2219.658,"duration":6.85},{"text":"But we were influenced by the fact that the creditors concerned were anxious for these -- both of these compromises to take place in order that the reorganization not be delayed.","start":2219.658,"stop":2234.772,"duration":15.11},{"text":"And this was a very important factor and we felt on -- from our examination of the facts and the dispute and everything and we still stand by it, that it was not the objections to the claim were not -- did not warrant litigation in view of the fairness of the proposed compromise.","start":2234.772,"stop":2256.681,"duration":21.91}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"But Mr. Simmons I can see how you could -- on your investigation becomes satisfied of that but how could the Court be satisfied of that if it didn't have a hearing on that conclusion on your part as compared with the reports of the SEC and the stockholders to the contrary?","start":2256.681,"stop":2280.13,"duration":23.45}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, we argued to the lower court that there were no basis for fraud chares that this was a factual matter and we would have the burden of proving that the breakdown of the vessels and all that was caused by Merrill-Stevens in spite of the fact that the vessel was accepted by the government authorities and everybody concern and put out to sea.","start":2280.13,"stop":2301.81,"duration":21.68},{"text":"We had weighed all of these things and we gave the results of our weighing of these matters to the Court.","start":2301.81,"stop":2308.869,"duration":7.06},{"text":"Now this is a way cases are settled, the -- but commonly we study the facts and you report and recommend to your client the basis of your settlement.","start":2308.869,"stop":2319.651,"duration":10.78},{"text":"We didn't try to spread all the facts and the reason before the Court except that conclusion on the matter.","start":2319.651,"stop":2327.279,"duration":7.63}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the SEC take a position on the Merrill -- whatever it is, claim?","start":2327.279,"stop":2333.87,"duration":6.59}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"They --","start":2333.87,"stop":2333.897,"duration":0.03}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Did they say -- did the SEC alleged that it was fraudulent that that was (Voice Overlap) --","start":2333.897,"stop":2336.902,"duration":3.01}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No, they never alleged that it was fraudulent.","start":2336.902,"stop":2339.215,"duration":2.31},{"text":"They merely alleged -- stated the objections.","start":2339.215,"stop":2344.201,"duration":4.99},{"text":"They stated there was -- they'd uncovered evidence to indicate that Merrill-Stevens was -- may have been guilty of negligence or breach of contract in some manner in performing the work on these vessels.","start":2344.201,"stop":2355.748,"duration":11.55}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"And did the Court ever go into that?","start":2355.748,"stop":2359.382,"duration":3.63}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"We never tried the matter except to consider and weigh the -- object the statements that Merrill's -- denials of Merrill-Stevens, the statements on the other side and then the Court considered the compromise which all of the creditors approved.","start":2359.382,"stop":2377.385,"duration":18},{"text":"Now all the creditors wanted the compromise very much.","start":2377.385,"stop":2379.674,"duration":2.29},{"text":"I think I've made that quiet clear.","start":2379.674,"stop":2381.059,"duration":1.39},{"text":"No creditor objected to the compromise and the creditors are the real parties in interest.","start":2381.059,"stop":2385.452,"duration":4.39},{"text":"They're the ones who would benefit by the compromise or would benefit by any recovery.","start":2385.452,"stop":2390.115,"duration":4.66},{"text":"It might be --","start":2390.115,"stop":2390.243,"duration":0.13}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the SEC object --","start":2390.243,"stop":2390.616,"duration":0.37}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"-- made against Merrill-Stevens.","start":2390.616,"stop":2392.242,"duration":1.63}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the SEC object to the compromise?","start":2392.242,"stop":2396.078,"duration":3.84}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2396.078,"stop":2396.567,"duration":0.49},{"text":"They have (Inaudible) and through here objected to the compromise, only on the basis that we -- that we didn't go in and tried the thing.","start":2396.567,"stop":2405.184,"duration":8.62},{"text":"Now, I want to -- we had to make a recommendation as to which, what we're going to try and what we're not going to try about all these claims that have been made against the data.","start":2405.184,"stop":2420.367,"duration":15.18},{"text":"And I want to -- my time is about up and I want to --","start":2420.367,"stop":2424.607,"duration":4.24}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"But what do you consider the SEC's role under the statute to be in the reorganization of this magnitude?","start":2424.607,"stop":2434.377,"duration":9.77}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"They are advisers to the Court and to the trustee, and they had been very helpful in a great many matters.","start":2434.377,"stop":2440.38,"duration":6}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I want to be a little more helpful here --","start":2440.38,"stop":2441.807,"duration":1.43}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"They -- I don't -- they --","start":2441.807,"stop":2442.063,"duration":0.26}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2442.063,"stop":2445.554,"duration":3.49}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"For some reason or other, the SEC here has made a kind of a crusade out of this case for these poor stockholders.","start":2445.554,"stop":2452.412,"duration":6.86},{"text":"We think that they should be just as concern or more concerned about the poor creditors because creditors come ahead of stockholders.","start":2452.412,"stop":2461.212,"duration":8.8},{"text":"And we've taken the position that the creditors are the real parties in interest.","start":2461.212,"stop":2465.292,"duration":4.08},{"text":"They want these compromises and they've approved this plan in overwhelming vote.","start":2465.292,"stop":2469.837,"duration":4.55},{"text":"The last count was about 98 or 95% approved and nobody disapproved.","start":2469.837,"stop":2475.645,"duration":5.81},{"text":"They want this plan.","start":2475.645,"stop":2476.819,"duration":1.17},{"text":"They want to get on with this reorganization.","start":2476.819,"stop":2479.01,"duration":2.19},{"text":"They don't want to take the time and go back and fight these claims out.","start":2479.01,"stop":2482.875,"duration":3.86},{"text":"This is a practical matter that they are concerned with.","start":2482.875,"stop":2492.385,"duration":9.51},{"text":"I do want to conclude by just pointing out one thing regarding the failure of the trustee to bring suits to recover damages against persons accused of fraudulent practices in connection with transactions involving TMT stock.","start":2492.385,"stop":2511.925,"duration":19.54},{"text":"Petitioner's brief makes a serious and unfounded charge against the trustee and against me.","start":2511.925,"stop":2518.422,"duration":6.5},{"text":"On page 30 of his brief, he says that for three years preceding 1965, trustee's counsel for that -- in 1965, trustee's counsel for the first time admitted the other abandonment of these suits.","start":2518.422,"stop":2537.567,"duration":19.14},{"text":"Now -- and on page 15 of petitioner's reply brief, he repeats his charge in the following language.","start":2537.567,"stop":2543.522,"duration":5.95},{"text":"The trustee failed to disclose on the record to the stockholders or creditors or the SEC that a secret understanding was actually made in 1962 to suppress the suits and waive the setoffs.","start":2543.522,"stop":2554.905,"duration":11.38},{"text":"This was disclosed as to the suits for the first time in 1965.","start":2554.905,"stop":2560.398,"duration":5.49},{"text":"And what they're referring to in 1965 is where in an answer to a question by Mr. Gonson of the SEC, he says there's a contemplated -- at all that the trustee of the estate would institute any litigation with respect to the Caplan mortgage transaction answered by Mr. Simmons, know that matter has been settled in the plan of reorganization.","start":2560.398,"stop":2583.246,"duration":22.85},{"text":"Now, I want to refer the Court to page 662 of the record, in record number 2, in which -- in April of 1962 when we were beginning to consider this plan of reorganization, this is the report that the trustee and I made to the Court.","start":2583.246,"stop":2605.669,"duration":22.42},{"text":"As to the contention of the stockholders committee that there are causes of action against Caplan and Merrill-Stevens, which could result in recoveries beyond the amount of the claims, that trustee has been advised that such possibility is too remote to warrant the expensive litigation and to delay in reorganization.","start":2605.669,"stop":2625.16,"duration":19.49},{"text":"The trustee has filed two suits as a result of his 1960 investigation of the Caplan mortgage participants and others who had dealings with the form of management.","start":2625.16,"stop":2634.354,"duration":9.19},{"text":"One of these suits is against Joseph Abrams and others involved in the purchase of the property at Wilmington, Delaware.","start":2634.354,"stop":2640.806,"duration":6.45},{"text":"The other is against Eric Rath (ph), former president-organizer of TMT, recovers in these suits are uncertain amount and they are the only ones considered worthy of prosecution.","start":2640.806,"stop":2655.712,"duration":14.91},{"text":"It was our opinion that in a reorganization case you have to look to the future and not to the past.","start":2655.712,"stop":2661.662,"duration":5.95},{"text":"The creditors wanted to get it on with reorganization and they did not want to waste the time of the -- time would be necessary and the expense in prosecuting these all -- suits in trying to punish all these people that may have been involved in the downfall of TMT.","start":2661.662,"stop":2680.39,"duration":18.73},{"text":"And this was our considered judgment and this was made a matter of record in connection with the hearings proceeding, the first consideration of the plan in 1962.","start":2680.39,"stop":2689.359,"duration":8.97}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"What happened to the Abrams in that suits?","start":2689.359,"stop":2692.857,"duration":3.5}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"We got a judgment against Mr. Rath (ph), the ringleader of the former management in the amount of a $131,000 in 1963 and we have not been able to collect 1-5 cent a piece on it.","start":2692.857,"stop":2706.741,"duration":13.88}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"How about the other one?","start":2706.741,"stop":2707.6,"duration":0.86}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The other suit is still pending in the Southern District Court of New York.","start":2707.6,"stop":2710.622,"duration":3.02},{"text":"Any benefits that it gets come under the plan will go to the common creditors of the company under the plan of reorganization.","start":2710.622,"stop":2719.552,"duration":8.93},{"text":"So far, we spent a lot of money on that suit and so far, we haven't gotten anywhere with it.","start":2719.552,"stop":2725.355,"duration":5.8},{"text":"It's not over with yet, but we've not recovered anything with it enough.","start":2725.355,"stop":2729.549,"duration":4.19},{"text":"Now those are the two suits that we brought and we considered all the rest of them.","start":2729.549,"stop":2734.744,"duration":5.2},{"text":"And I'm not -- brought anymore because we didn't feel that they warranted -- the merits of them didn't warrant it, the expense was not warranted and the delay in the reorganization case was not warranted.","start":2734.744,"stop":2748.685,"duration":13.94}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"That makes -- see if I can clarify this in my on line, did there come a point of time at which the Court, the judge not the trustee, the Court, gave to the Stockholders Committee and the SEC an opportunity to present on the record evidence that it had with respect to claims that might be asserted against these -- to a creditor party.","start":2748.685,"stop":2787.645,"duration":38.96}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No, because the facts --","start":2787.645,"stop":2789.188,"duration":1.54},{"text":"No, because the facts with respect to those objections were well-developed in the various investigation that were made to be --","start":2789.188,"stop":2797.772,"duration":8.58}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but that's by the trustee.","start":2797.772,"stop":2799.507,"duration":1.74},{"text":"I've got the answer to my question.","start":2799.507,"stop":2801.233,"duration":1.73},{"text":"Thank you.","start":2801.233,"stop":2802.544,"duration":1.31}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No, they were no.","start":2802.544,"stop":2803.671,"duration":1.13},{"text":"They were not.","start":2803.671,"stop":2805.982,"duration":2.31},{"text":"The rest of my time will be taken -- of our time will be taken by Mr. Spitzer.","start":2805.982,"stop":2811.766,"duration":5.78}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Very well.","start":2811.766,"stop":2814.757,"duration":2.99}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice --","start":2814.757,"stop":2816.028,"duration":1.27}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Spitzer.","start":2816.028,"stop":2818.206,"duration":2.18}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"May it please the Court.","start":2818.206,"stop":2821.556,"duration":3.35},{"text":"It's perhaps a searing emotional experience to sit at the counsel table of this Court and because one is an (Inaudible) trustee to find oneself receiving the phrasal and invective employed yesterday.","start":2821.556,"stop":2841.064,"duration":19.51},{"text":"I suppose if one could be objective about it, would be alleviated by knowing that everybody else connected with this proceeding whether it be the trustee, its counsel, the creditors, even to some extent, the District Court and even some members of the panel of the -- the panels that sat in the Fifth Court of Appeals are included.","start":2841.064,"stop":2863.767,"duration":22.7},{"text":"Perhaps it mitigates, it doesn't eliminate it.","start":2863.767,"stop":2866.86,"duration":3.09},{"text":"And if there's any emotion in my argument, I hope the Court will indulge me.","start":2866.86,"stop":2872.265,"duration":5.4},{"text":"I appear solely on behalf of the Caplan mortgage claim.","start":2872.265,"stop":2878.904,"duration":6.64},{"text":"Your Honors will find in the briefs which is so highly critical, there isn't a word as to the nature of those claims, of that claim.","start":2878.904,"stop":2886.935,"duration":8.03},{"text":"Some $330,000 and fresh new money, it was paid for a note in that amount secured by two mortgages for plainly disclosed investors and for shares of stock having a described value of $49,500.","start":2886.935,"stop":2902.38,"duration":15.45},{"text":"A little over two-thirds of that money was immediately on the direction of the data transmitted to the (Inaudible) National Bank to pay for an installment of interest in principal on a maritime mortgage guaranteed by the United States Maritime Administration and thereby redounded for the benefit of the Government by reducing its liability.","start":2902.38,"stop":2922.368,"duration":19.99},{"text":"The greater part of the balance was used to clear liens and libels on other vessels to which it would now be subject.","start":2922.368,"stop":2930.137,"duration":7.77},{"text":"The claim presently would be something substantially, substantially in excess of a half million dollars with interest at a 6% rate provided for in the note.","start":2930.137,"stop":2941.264,"duration":11.13},{"text":"This has been settled for the sum of $250,000 with the interest subordinated to that of a general claim with no voice whatsoever in the reorganized corporation, except as a minority stockholder having roughly 3% of the outstanding stock.","start":2941.264,"stop":2959.22,"duration":17.96},{"text":"Let me it very plain irrespective of what the brief say.","start":2959.22,"stop":2962.098,"duration":2.88},{"text":"The plan is clear, the record is clear.","start":2962.098,"stop":2964.906,"duration":2.81},{"text":"We never sought, we never obtained and there has been no disposition of any claims against any participant.","start":2964.906,"stop":2972.507,"duration":7.6},{"text":"I appear here solely on behalf of the trustees.","start":2972.507,"stop":2976.167,"duration":3.66},{"text":"If the data or state desires to sue any individual participant, we have never blocked it.","start":2976.167,"stop":2981.652,"duration":5.49},{"text":"I want to be also clear on one thing.","start":2981.652,"stop":2984.485,"duration":2.83},{"text":"The position of the Caplan mortgage trustees from the inception has been plain.","start":2984.485,"stop":2988.789,"duration":4.3},{"text":"We immediately filed a claim.","start":2988.789,"stop":2991.358,"duration":2.57},{"text":"We made opposition claim, we said we were first mortgagees, subject and subordinate to no claims.","start":2991.358,"stop":2998.668,"duration":7.31},{"text":"For two and a half years, neither petitioner nor the SEC filed any objections whatsoever to our client.","start":2998.668,"stop":3007.575,"duration":8.91},{"text":"A plan of reorganization was promulgated which incorporated a compromise, not at our request.","start":3007.575,"stop":3014.179,"duration":6.6},{"text":"We have never once requested any compromise on our claim.","start":3014.179,"stop":3018.716,"duration":4.54},{"text":"We have manfully stood up and taken our position and read -- and been ready to defend it.","start":3018.716,"stop":3023.922,"duration":5.21},{"text":"It was only after we petitioned for a leave to foreclose.","start":3023.922,"stop":3028.626,"duration":4.7},{"text":"When it was denied we went to the Court of Appeals.","start":3028.626,"stop":3031.24,"duration":2.61},{"text":"The Court of Appeals reversed, remanded and directed that we be satisfied.","start":3031.24,"stop":3035.672,"duration":4.43},{"text":"When the Court referred it to a special master, we took a second appeal.","start":3035.672,"stop":3039.384,"duration":3.71},{"text":"And during the pendency of that appeal, the trustee and the creditors requested that we compromise.","start":3039.384,"stop":3044.474,"duration":5.09},{"text":"We were prepared to accept the compromise or litigate.","start":3044.474,"stop":3047.739,"duration":3.26},{"text":"The matter was incorporated in a plan of reorganization which was approved and confirmed and let me make it plain.","start":3047.739,"stop":3054.001,"duration":6.26},{"text":"There was no objection of any kind to our claim at this point by anyone.","start":3054.001,"stop":3061.151,"duration":7.15},{"text":"When the plan was ready to be consummated, the SEC requested an investigation of our claim.","start":3061.151,"stop":3067.204,"duration":6.05},{"text":"We immediately consented in any form, manner or shape that was sought.","start":3067.204,"stop":3072.686,"duration":5.48},{"text":"There was an investigation that took place from January 29 to May 4, 1960.","start":3072.686,"stop":3079.095,"duration":6.41},{"text":"It was conducted by the reorganization and trustee and his counsel and by four members of the staff of the SEC, two of their attorneys and two of their investigators.","start":3079.095,"stop":3090.484,"duration":11.39},{"text":"There was some 33 persons interrogated.","start":3090.484,"stop":3093.927,"duration":3.44},{"text":"There was some 2200 pages of testimony transcribed.","start":3093.927,"stop":3098.601,"duration":4.67},{"text":"There was some 60 exhibits that were introduced in evidence.","start":3098.601,"stop":3102.864,"duration":4.26},{"text":"And while we flatly disagreed with the conclusion of the reorganization trustee, at least he was fair enough to say that the Caplan mortgage trustees and the participants gave every possible cooperation, we testified everything that was asked for, we produced every record that was sought.","start":3102.864,"stop":3122.213,"duration":19.35},{"text":"May I say to Your Honors that when the Court originally passed upon the plan of reorganization incorporating our compromise of our claim it had before it everything that the combined and cumulative efforts of counsel for the trustee, counsel for the SEC, counsel for the creditors and counsel for the petitioner could bring before the Court.","start":3122.213,"stop":3148.743,"duration":26.53},{"text":"Now in one respect, I see I have only five minutes and I'd hope I'd have more.","start":3148.743,"stop":3153.404,"duration":4.66},{"text":"In one respect I must disagree with Mr. Simmons with respect to our claim.","start":3153.404,"stop":3160.578,"duration":7.17},{"text":"The charges of fraud whenever refuted as what stated yesterday, we filed a claim, there was no objection filed.","start":3160.578,"stop":3166.882,"duration":6.3},{"text":"Now, let me tell you exactly what transpired and there -- what hearings with respect to our claim before the Court.","start":3166.882,"stop":3173.297,"duration":6.41},{"text":"On April 24th, 1962, after the plan was -- the present plan was prepared, eight days before it was submitted for approval, counsel for the petitioner interrogated the trustee with respect to outstanding litigation and claims that would be litigated and it went into causes of action, patent claims, the Wilmington transaction and Merrill-Stevens.","start":3173.297,"stop":3196.737,"duration":23.44},{"text":"And I say to Your Honors that not one question was propounded with respect to any defense to our claim or to any claims against our participants.","start":3196.737,"stop":3208.141,"duration":11.4},{"text":"Eight days later, the plan came up for approval.","start":3208.141,"stop":3211.234,"duration":3.09},{"text":"Again, petitioner's counsel interrogated.","start":3211.234,"stop":3214.319,"duration":3.09},{"text":"There wasn't again one question asked with respect to our claim and this was when it was before the Court.","start":3214.319,"stop":3221.027,"duration":6.71},{"text":"Now with respect to the SEC on the approval, the SEC's counsel questioned the trustee as to what were his reasons for approving this compromised provision.","start":3221.027,"stop":3234.528,"duration":13.5},{"text":"The Court stated that it had a jury waiting to come in, it had another case ready for the afternoon.","start":3234.528,"stop":3240.044,"duration":5.52},{"text":"And if there was time desired to review this matter, it would set the matter down for another day.","start":3240.044,"stop":3245.691,"duration":5.65},{"text":"At this point, SEC counsel stated and I quote from record 2, page 283, speaking for my self Your Honor, I have concluded.","start":3245.691,"stop":3257.3,"duration":11.61},{"text":"Now it is asserted in the reply brief that we imply that they were satisfied.","start":3257.3,"stop":3261.611,"duration":4.31},{"text":"I make no implication.","start":3261.611,"stop":3263.19,"duration":1.58},{"text":"Satisfied or not, they had the opportunity.","start":3263.19,"stop":3266.575,"duration":3.38},{"text":"They were requested by the Court, If you want this matter set down for a day certain, we will do it but they didn't want it.","start":3266.575,"stop":3271.933,"duration":5.36},{"text":"What they wanted really was and they then requested the trustee of state, how did they arrive at the compromise which he stated.","start":3271.933,"stop":3281.527,"duration":9.59},{"text":"The Court then submitted a memorandum at a later date that there was insufficient on the record of proof.This was not the end of it.","start":3281.527,"stop":3289.331,"duration":7.8},{"text":"This was in 1962.","start":3289.331,"stop":3291.37,"duration":2.04},{"text":"The matter went up to the Court of Appeals and at that time, the counsel for the trustee set forth the various reasons for the compromise of our claim.","start":3291.37,"stop":3299.826,"duration":8.46},{"text":"There was a reversal, as Your Honors know, because of the priority status of the Government's nontax claims.","start":3299.826,"stop":3306.739,"duration":6.91},{"text":"When the matter was remanded and came before the Court again, on November 4th, 1964 SEC counsel inquired as to the general manager whether any attempt had been made to negotiate a more favorable settlement.","start":3306.739,"stop":3321.887,"duration":15.15},{"text":"It was answered.","start":3321.887,"stop":3323.194,"duration":1.31},{"text":"No effort whatsoever was made to impugn the settlement.","start":3323.194,"stop":3328.521,"duration":5.33},{"text":"They disagree with the reasons for the settlement to request us to appear and testify and we've been ready on any and every occasion or to produce any testimony whatsoever.","start":3328.521,"stop":3339.272,"duration":10.75},{"text":"There was a further hearing on January 19th, 1965 where SEC counsel inquired the reorganization trustee's counsel as to the status of litigation even with respect to the Caplan mortgage claim.","start":3339.272,"stop":3352.913,"duration":13.64},{"text":"Again, there was no request for any interrogation, any criticism whatsoever with respect to this compromised provision.","start":3352.913,"stop":3360.842,"duration":7.93},{"text":"And during all these period, petitioner's counsel which portrays itself fulfilling such a heroic role in uncovering all these matters stood there silent (Inaudible).","start":3360.842,"stop":3372.205,"duration":11.36},{"text":"No interrogation, no inquiry whatsoever.","start":3372.205,"stop":3375.899,"duration":3.69},{"text":"I say to Your Honors that the contention that this record is inadequate or that the District Court acted improvidently with respect to our claim and I am here only on behalf of our claim is absolutely incorrect.","start":3375.899,"stop":3388.619,"duration":12.72},{"text":"And may I make it perfectly plain that the United States Government, which is the -- one of the largest creditors, has not objected to this provision.","start":3388.619,"stop":3399.728,"duration":11.11},{"text":"And may I also add one further thing with respect to the Government.","start":3399.728,"stop":3403.375,"duration":3.65},{"text":"In 1959, the United States Department of Justice, at a hearing before the Court, set forth on the record that it had made an investigation of our claim that it had interrogated our representatives.","start":3403.375,"stop":3416.995,"duration":13.62},{"text":"With our consent had gone through all books, records and documents and were thoroughly satisfied with respect to this claim.","start":3416.995,"stop":3424.795,"duration":7.8},{"text":"I know that I can't go further that I had wanted to present certain -- the aspect of the two, Your Honors.","start":3424.795,"stop":3430.063,"duration":5.27},{"text":"I merely want to point out to you that we are in this position at this time.","start":3430.063,"stop":3434.541,"duration":4.48},{"text":"We have compromised twice, thinking that we had eliminated the problem, apparently we haven't.","start":3434.541,"stop":3441.615,"duration":7.07},{"text":"We have surrendered our mortgages at the direction of the District Court.","start":3441.615,"stop":3447.065,"duration":5.45},{"text":"We no longer even have those.","start":3447.065,"stop":3449.347,"duration":2.28},{"text":"Our property is now subject and subordinate to a mortgage that was issued to fulfill and consummate this plan of reorganization to that mortgage.","start":3449.347,"stop":3459.417,"duration":10.07},{"text":"Neither the SEC nor the petitioner objected.","start":3459.417,"stop":3462.206,"duration":2.79},{"text":"We are afforded in an absolutely untenable position as a result of no efforts on our part.","start":3462.206,"stop":3468.049,"duration":5.84},{"text":"We have done nothing to deserve this situation today.","start":3468.049,"stop":3471.285,"duration":3.24},{"text":"We have been prepared to substantiate our position.","start":3471.285,"stop":3474.702,"duration":3.42},{"text":"We have filed our claim.","start":3474.702,"stop":3476.076,"duration":1.37},{"text":"We have been ready to fight and we have never been afforded the opportunity to do so.","start":3476.076,"stop":3481.79,"duration":5.71}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"To what conclusion does all that leads you in terms --","start":3481.79,"stop":3485.255,"duration":3.47}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm sorry sir.","start":3485.255,"stop":3486.366,"duration":1.11}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"To what conclusion does that leads you in terms of what this Court intended?","start":3486.366,"stop":3491.081,"duration":4.72},{"text":"I should suppose for example, your position is that -- your claim was thoroughly considered before the Court and everybody had an opportunity in exhausting this opportunity to say what he had to say before the Court.","start":3491.081,"stop":3505.734,"duration":14.65},{"text":"Supposed that we're not true with respect to the Merrill-Stevens' claim.","start":3505.734,"stop":3511.085,"duration":5.35},{"text":"If that were not true and suppose that this Court should conclude, I have no idea whether it will (Inaudible), that the absence of those hearings as surprisingly hears with respect with the Merrill-Stevens' claim is a violation or the correct rule of procedure, then don't we have to set the whole plan aside?","start":3511.085,"stop":3535.972,"duration":24.89}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"It would seem to me, Mr. Justice Fortas, that as a mater of fundamental equity here, our position should be preserved.","start":3535.972,"stop":3542.441,"duration":6.47}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"How could that --","start":3542.441,"stop":3542.485,"duration":0.04}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"We cannot --","start":3542.485,"stop":3543.191,"duration":0.71}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":3543.191,"stop":3543.418,"duration":0.23},{"text":"What I'm asking is -- I appreciate your argument and of course the clarity of it, whatever I asked you is, how can we do it?","start":3543.418,"stop":3553.719,"duration":10.3},{"text":"What do you -- asking us to do?","start":3553.719,"stop":3556.296,"duration":2.58}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it would seem to me that this matter, at least with respect to our claim having been compromised and the adjusted therefore full and complete and adequate hearings in the record, that compromise should stand.","start":3556.296,"stop":3566.673,"duration":10.38},{"text":"We cannot at this point be restored to our position.","start":3566.673,"stop":3570.429,"duration":3.76},{"text":"Our mortgages cannot be reinstated because that may now be intervening equities, which no court I think that it could eliminate.","start":3570.429,"stop":3576.772,"duration":6.34}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that.","start":3576.772,"stop":3578.55,"duration":1.78}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"And it seems to me irrespective of what may have and I don't know what happened or what the Court's position will be but we should be preserved in the fulfillment of the compromise which we have in good faith carried out.","start":3578.55,"stop":3590.783,"duration":12.23}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"But you don't know how we could do it?","start":3590.783,"stop":3593.286,"duration":2.5}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"You're the justice of the Supreme Court and I am not.","start":3593.286,"stop":3596.06,"duration":2.77},{"text":"I'm not (Inaudible) --","start":3596.06,"stop":3599.556,"duration":3.5}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that but the --","start":3599.556,"stop":3600.362,"duration":0.81}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"This is the first laugh I've gotten out of this proceeding so forgive me.","start":3600.362,"stop":3605.158,"duration":4.8}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that but we're trying to find out whether you -- your verifying that statement here ended in a specific conclusion of whether it was an admonition, has to do the right thing.","start":3605.158,"stop":3621.814,"duration":16.66}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, I am not so presumptuous as to admonish this Court.","start":3621.814,"stop":3625.155,"duration":3.34},{"text":"I do believe that under Section 27, there has been a compromise made.","start":3625.155,"stop":3630.013,"duration":4.86},{"text":"It has fulfilled all the requirements and if other provisions of the plan do not stand, this compromise should be honored and respected and at least built in within any type of agreement.","start":3630.013,"stop":3641.142,"duration":11.13}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you have the -- you've been paid the amount of your settlement, I take it?","start":3641.142,"stop":3644.648,"duration":3.51}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":3644.648,"stop":3645.121,"duration":0.47}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"You have the money?","start":3645.121,"stop":3645.947,"duration":0.83}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir and we are holding the money.","start":3645.947,"stop":3647.847,"duration":1.9}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"And setting aside the plan isn't going to get to -- isn't going to make you -- give that money back --","start":3647.847,"stop":3653.67,"duration":5.82}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"Except Your Honor please, if I may intrude.","start":3653.67,"stop":3656.754,"duration":3.08},{"text":"What do we do to preserve our situation in enforcing it in any subsequent proceeding?","start":3656.754,"stop":3661.263,"duration":4.51},{"text":"We no longer --","start":3661.263,"stop":3661.415,"duration":0.15}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand --","start":3661.415,"stop":3662.011,"duration":0.6}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"-- have our mortgages and they've been satisfied --","start":3662.011,"stop":3663.686,"duration":1.68}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that.","start":3663.686,"stop":3664.349,"duration":0.66}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"-- and they're probably has been subordinated.","start":3664.349,"stop":3666.157,"duration":1.81}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that.","start":3666.157,"stop":3667.122,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"So how can we preserve our position in any further proceedings?","start":3667.122,"stop":3671.732,"duration":4.61},{"text":"We are at this point not in the position where we can assert the lien claim that we had.","start":3671.732,"stop":3676.688,"duration":4.96},{"text":"And I don't think that there is the power in this Court or any other court to restore it now.","start":3676.688,"stop":3680.588,"duration":3.9}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, I think that that's true but do you have the $250,000?","start":3680.588,"stop":3685.284,"duration":4.7}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"We have $250,000, yes, sir.","start":3685.284,"stop":3688.019,"duration":2.73},{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":3688.019,"stop":3688.547,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"As long as you keep it, you're satisfied.","start":3688.547,"stop":3691.769,"duration":3.22}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":3691.769,"stop":3692.796,"duration":1.03},{"text":"We compromise it and we're prepared to stand on that compromise.","start":3692.796,"stop":3695.736,"duration":2.94}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Well did somebody tried to get a background, do you got it?","start":3695.736,"stop":3699.455,"duration":3.72}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, but on the other hand, we don't want (Voice Overlap) --","start":3699.455,"stop":3701.672,"duration":2.22}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"You'd like to know that nobody could.","start":3701.672,"stop":3703.385,"duration":1.71}]},{"speakerName":"M. James Spitzer","textObjs":[{"text":"I'd like to know that I'm not going to be in violation of any order of a court.","start":3703.385,"stop":3706.531,"duration":3.15},{"text":"I'll be subjected to further proceeding.","start":3706.531,"stop":3708.31,"duration":1.78},{"text":"Yes, sir, this is also important to us.","start":3708.31,"stop":3712.236,"duration":3.93}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Very well Mr. Spitzer.","start":3712.236,"stop":3716.695,"duration":4.46},{"text":"Mr. Langbein.","start":3716.695,"stop":3720.875,"duration":4.18}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court.","start":3720.875,"stop":3724.507,"duration":3.63},{"text":"I'm going to reply only very briefly to Mr. Spitzer's discussion.","start":3724.507,"stop":3728.893,"duration":4.39}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"A little louder if you please.","start":3728.893,"stop":3729.692,"duration":0.8}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm going to reply only very briefly, sir to Mr. Spitzer's discussion.","start":3729.692,"stop":3735.379,"duration":5.69},{"text":"Because most of it is what I characterized yesterday as bickering in the responding brief and also answered by more bickering I'm afraid in our reply brief.","start":3735.379,"stop":3747.094,"duration":11.72},{"text":"We have attempted to set out specific citations to the record that places of which we think Mr. Spitzer is in error in his view of what was actually in the record.","start":3747.094,"stop":3762.261,"duration":15.17}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"In what way?","start":3762.261,"stop":3764.624,"duration":2.36}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"I say, sir that Mr. Spitzer cannot come here and talk about equities when all compromises, when our position on it, Mr. Justice Black, is not on the merits of the mortgage.","start":3764.624,"stop":3782.115,"duration":17.49},{"text":"He may have a good mortgage; he may have a bad mortgage.","start":3782.115,"stop":3785.713,"duration":3.6},{"text":"Our position on it from the first was that he was not or his clients were not in any position of being able to assert their commercial rights under the mortgage because they were in fact acting as cloaks for people who wrecked this company.","start":3785.713,"stop":3807.276,"duration":21.56},{"text":"And that no matter what the commercial situation with respect to the mortgage, the trustee at first brought that very bitterly that they cannot estop anybody because they are covers for frauds.This was a position that we wondered about to begin with.","start":3807.276,"stop":3826.973,"duration":19.7},{"text":"Very early in the proceedings, Mr. Spitzer was asked in open court, Is there is Mr. Joe Abrams interested in or who is a part of that group?,referring to his settings.","start":3826.973,"stop":3843.49,"duration":16.52},{"text":"Mr. Spitzer: There is no Joe -- Mr. Joe Abrams in our group.","start":3843.49,"stop":3847.825,"duration":4.34},{"text":"He has an interest in I believe in -- no there is not.","start":3847.825,"stop":3852.697,"duration":4.87},{"text":"No.","start":3852.697,"stop":3856.185,"duration":3.49},{"text":"So, at that point, there was a disclaimer of any interest by -- in the group by the man who was primarily along with his other client, Mr. Shaffer, so the trustee found in his ultimate investigation the prime record of this company.","start":3856.185,"stop":3879.473,"duration":23.29},{"text":"It was only when we turned up evidence which we tended to the trustee in which he rejected that there really was a Joe Abrams behind this and when the SEC turned up more evidence that ultimately the trustee was forced to set aside his first plan which it turned the whole company over to these people.","start":3879.473,"stop":3904.467,"duration":24.99},{"text":"Now, this is the reason that we say that they cannot be in a position of saying, We're innocent equity people here.","start":3904.467,"stop":3914.74,"duration":10.27},{"text":"We have equities with us.","start":3914.74,"stop":3917.542,"duration":2.8},{"text":"We were sucked into a compromise.","start":3917.542,"stop":3921.534,"duration":3.99},{"text":"We say that they were sucked into a compromise, the terms of that compromise whenever fully disclosed.","start":3921.534,"stop":3928.633,"duration":7.1},{"text":"The basis for that compromise was never fully disclosed as I argued yesterday.","start":3928.633,"stop":3933.574,"duration":4.94},{"text":"What right therefore do they have to sit here innocently and say, Everybody is estopped?","start":3933.574,"stop":3939.991,"duration":6.42}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Didn't you have --","start":3939.991,"stop":3940.316,"duration":0.32}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"We made a deal.\"","start":3940.316,"stop":3941.255,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Didn't you have plenty of opportunity at various stages in this proceeding to present whatever fact to the Court you wanted to, that you wanted to?","start":3941.255,"stop":3951.007,"duration":9.75}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"With respect to --","start":3951.007,"stop":3952.081,"duration":1.07}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"To this particular settlement of the Caplan, the mortgage claim?","start":3952.081,"stop":3957.855,"duration":5.77}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"We didn't know what the detail facts of the settlement were.","start":3957.855,"stop":3961.325,"duration":3.47},{"text":"We had presented all the facts of the fraud.","start":3961.325,"stop":3964.282,"duration":2.96},{"text":"We had presented or the trustee had finally (Voice Overlap) --","start":3964.282,"stop":3966.203,"duration":1.92}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Did you have an opportunity to ask the trustee on the stand or --","start":3966.203,"stop":3971.404,"duration":5.2}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes we did, Your Honor.","start":3971.404,"stop":3972.723,"duration":1.32}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Did you ask him?","start":3972.723,"stop":3973.875,"duration":1.15}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, we did.","start":3973.875,"stop":3974.816,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"So did you --","start":3974.816,"stop":3975.02,"duration":0.2}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"There was a passage (Voice Overlap) --","start":3975.02,"stop":3975.376,"duration":0.36}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"-- did you pursue it or did you find out all you wanted to know?","start":3975.376,"stop":3977.873,"duration":2.5},{"text":"He didn't --","start":3977.873,"stop":3978.064,"duration":0.19}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":3978.064,"stop":3978.163,"duration":0.1}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"-- refuse to say -- tell you, did he?","start":3978.163,"stop":3979.931,"duration":1.77}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"No, he misleds.","start":3979.931,"stop":3982.05,"duration":2.12},{"text":"There's a passage in the record in which he was (Voice Overlap) --","start":3982.05,"stop":3984.623,"duration":2.57}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"But he still had an opportunity to --","start":3984.623,"stop":3986.225,"duration":1.6}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":3986.225,"stop":3987.371,"duration":1.15}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"-- question him, find out all you wanted to the --","start":3987.371,"stop":3989.329,"duration":1.96}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, let me just read what happened here, sir.","start":3989.329,"stop":3993.81,"duration":4.48},{"text":"He was asked regarding the alleged compromises of the Shaffer-Spitzer mortgage claim and the Merrill-Stevens claim, would you give us some indication as to the basis of this compromises.","start":3993.81,"stop":4005.136,"duration":11.33},{"text":"Now this was after the facts were out, that there was a fraud here permitted by their Shaffer-Spitzer principle.","start":4005.136,"stop":4011.793,"duration":6.66}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Could you please talk into the --","start":4011.793,"stop":4013.203,"duration":1.41}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm sorry, sir.","start":4013.203,"stop":4014.385,"duration":1.18},{"text":"I'll be glad to, he says, I'll be glad to.","start":4014.385,"stop":4017.244,"duration":2.86},{"text":"And on the next page, he's asked again about Shaffer-Spitzer and he says, The compromise of a claim, the Caplan claim, was worked out between the attorney for the group, my attorney and myself was done in conference; all three of us had with the Court, completed after deliberations, negotiations, submitted to the Court, approved by the Court.","start":4017.244,"stop":4039.156,"duration":21.91},{"text":"That's the way we came about to reach that compromise.","start":4039.156,"stop":4042.482,"duration":3.33},{"text":"So he states where it happened, in chambers --","start":4042.482,"stop":4045.851,"duration":3.37}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, why didn't you (Voice Overlap) --","start":4045.851,"stop":4046.227,"duration":0.38}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Who was there --","start":4046.227,"stop":4047.193,"duration":0.97}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Why didn't you pursue it?","start":4047.193,"stop":4049.437,"duration":2.24}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"We didn't pursue for the reason that the Court at that very point was telling everybody, Look, I have a jury coming in here.","start":4049.437,"stop":4057.649,"duration":8.21},{"text":"I can't sit around here all day and listen to wrangling about this.","start":4057.649,"stop":4061.346,"duration":3.7},{"text":"You can submit a memorandum.","start":4061.346,"stop":4062.685,"duration":1.34},{"text":"And the SEC submitted a memorandum in which it raised this very point and we joined in the memorandum.","start":4062.685,"stop":4068.59,"duration":5.91}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"So you objected the approval of the -- to the approval to compromise on the basis that -- on the basis stated by the trustee?","start":4068.59,"stop":4077.962,"duration":9.37}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't understand the question.","start":4077.962,"stop":4078.393,"duration":0.43}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you -- as ultimately objected to the compromise?","start":4078.393,"stop":4080.95,"duration":2.56}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"We objected to it beforehand and we were --","start":4080.95,"stop":4083.024,"duration":2.07}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"And in the memorandum that you joined in further objection.","start":4083.024,"stop":4085.862,"duration":2.84}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Further objections.","start":4085.862,"stop":4087.392,"duration":1.53},{"text":"We objected to it when the plan first came out.","start":4087.392,"stop":4089.873,"duration":2.48},{"text":"We said you can have a plan with these compromises in them uninvestigated, with the basis not stated.","start":4089.873,"stop":4097.616,"duration":7.74},{"text":"Then when Mr. Gonson, SEC counsel, made this direct inquiry, what's the basis?","start":4097.616,"stop":4105.337,"duration":7.72},{"text":"I read the answer.","start":4105.337,"stop":4108.252,"duration":2.91},{"text":"And on -- we said the same thing and made these objections again not alone at approval time, at a confirmation time, at appeal time on both the version of the final plan that was -- what we call the second plan and the version of plan that we call (Voice Overlap) --","start":4108.252,"stop":4127.197,"duration":18.94}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, did you ever ask the judge to set the matter down for a further hearing?","start":4127.197,"stop":4131.966,"duration":4.77},{"text":"What -- in that memorandum the SEC filed within -- which you joined.","start":4131.966,"stop":4135.332,"duration":3.37},{"text":"You objected to the compromise and there hadn't been inadequate here -- basis for -- that you asked for --","start":4135.332,"stop":4142.487,"duration":7.15}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"We objected to all --","start":4142.487,"stop":4143.34,"duration":0.85}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"-- further -- for a further hearing?","start":4143.34,"stop":4143.877,"duration":0.54}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"We objected to all of these points.","start":4143.877,"stop":4146.698,"duration":2.82},{"text":"I can't tell the Court that we said that there had to be a further hearing after there was an order of approval came out.","start":4146.698,"stop":4154.654,"duration":7.96},{"text":"We'd raise the same points again and again and again, we'd ask the hearings on them again and again and again particularly with respect to the Merrill-Stevens claim and we had insisted throughout this proceeding.","start":4154.654,"stop":4174.294,"duration":19.64},{"text":"One further point should be mentioned here.","start":4174.294,"stop":4176.953,"duration":2.66},{"text":"We are a committee.","start":4176.953,"stop":4178.827,"duration":1.87},{"text":"We are intended to be holding a watching brief.","start":4178.827,"stop":4182.38,"duration":3.55},{"text":"It is our responsibility to the people whom we represent, some 7000 stockholders, who have paid many millions of dollars under this fraudulent scheme to float stock, how much of it reached the company ultimately.","start":4182.38,"stop":4198.361,"duration":15.98},{"text":"It doesn't appear in the record but we know from the extent of the record that has been made, a good deal of it, many hundreds of thousand dollars of it were (Inaudible).","start":4198.361,"stop":4208.188,"duration":9.83},{"text":"Our position here is to point out what needs to be done, to suggest what needs to be done, to try and do it if it isn't done.","start":4208.188,"stop":4220.092,"duration":11.9},{"text":"But when we are blocked, at that point it becomes the Court's own responsibility under the decisions of this Court to take an affirmative responsibility for the fairness of a plan which is his duty under Chapter X.","start":4220.092,"stop":4234.973,"duration":14.88},{"text":"Whether we object before, during or after and we did.","start":4234.973,"stop":4240.451,"duration":5.48},{"text":"We think we've done all that we needed to do as the Court's responsibility and the trustee's fiduciary responsibility.","start":4240.451,"stop":4247.554,"duration":7.1},{"text":"Let me turn more directly now, if I may, to Mr. Simmons' position.","start":4247.554,"stop":4255.569,"duration":8.02},{"text":"I'd like to address myself to something he said at the very start of his discussion which he said it's going to be necessary for this Court to read all seven volumes of this record.","start":4255.569,"stop":4267.801,"duration":12.23},{"text":"I'm afraid as I said yesterday that it was going to be necessary for the Court to read a little more of this record than I would like to have read just because of these matters of detail of the fact.","start":4267.801,"stop":4279.557,"duration":11.76},{"text":"But none of it is the kind of thing that this Court ordinarily refuses to read by way of looking over to see whether or not a District Judge has made appropriate findings of fact on an issue presented to him.","start":4279.557,"stop":4299.103,"duration":19.55},{"text":"Of course there are disputes of fact.","start":4299.103,"stop":4302.921,"duration":3.82},{"text":"Mr. Simmons insists that there never wasn't a -- any real charges of fraud by us against Merrill-Stevens.","start":4302.921,"stop":4311.612,"duration":8.69},{"text":"And all we can do is ask the Court to read our specifications in which we say that they joined themselves in with the basic Shaffer-Spitzer we call it, it could just as well be called Abrams and Shaffer because they are the ultimate defrauders.","start":4311.612,"stop":4331.128,"duration":19.52},{"text":"Mr. Shaffer and Mr. Spitzer in our view are merely gnawing close for Shaffer himself and Abrams as himself on it.","start":4331.128,"stop":4345.713,"duration":14.59},{"text":"We objected to the claim on fraud grounds because there were misrepresentation as to this Carib Queen as to her speed, her performance, whether or not she'd been mortgaged out.","start":4345.713,"stop":4358.486,"duration":12.77},{"text":"All these matters that were essential to the fraud.","start":4358.486,"stop":4361.112,"duration":2.63},{"text":"This, the Court will have to read.","start":4361.112,"stop":4364.005,"duration":2.89},{"text":"Likewise, I think the Court is going to have to just see whether I'm right or whether Mr. Spitzer is right when he says both in his brief and here that the group behind the Shaffer-Spitzer mortgage was plainly disclosed.","start":4364.005,"stop":4382.322,"duration":18.32},{"text":"The briefs themselves operators and indexed to the record.","start":4382.322,"stop":4385.433,"duration":3.11},{"text":"But the most important thing that I'd do want to state with respect to this question of how much you have to read is really an answer to the question that I started to answer yesterday when Justice Fortas asked me about it.","start":4385.433,"stop":4396.115,"duration":10.68},{"text":"But what do we want here?","start":4396.115,"stop":4398.559,"duration":2.44},{"text":"It's our position that nothing that we want is going to require this Court to review and reverse determinations of fact made by the District Court even where we asked for review of something that is a mix batch in effect in law, the matter of insolvency evaluation.","start":4398.559,"stop":4425.992,"duration":27.43},{"text":"What we're objecting to there is the adoption and the enforcement of a rule of law by the District Court which we say is in -- just counter distinction to the rules of law that this Court had always enforced and said in the area of evaluation.","start":4425.992,"stop":4450.302,"duration":24.31},{"text":"That it is necessarily a matter of future, I think that it is necessarily a matter or probability and that all evidence which now exists bearing on the future earnings of the company must be presented to the Court.","start":4450.302,"stop":4469.181,"duration":18.88},{"text":"And for that reason we say that it is not necessary to discuss even on this one question which might be of question of fact, any of the detailed underlying facts because the facts are really admitted in here.","start":4469.181,"stop":4483.824,"duration":14.64},{"text":"The disputes of facts are fringed disputes.","start":4483.824,"stop":4487.835,"duration":4.01},{"text":"The facts of the case are undisputed on that, that you cannot value we think a company, which during the reorganization has grown from 300 to 600 trailers from three to five ships as this Court -- the District Court insisted it be valued.","start":4487.835,"stop":4507.302,"duration":19.47},{"text":"As it is now, a three-ship company, when their turning away business all the time and find new ships and planning improved ships and spending estate money on those plans and spending a estate time on those plans, this is a matter of law, this is not a matter of fact.","start":4507.302,"stop":4526.906,"duration":19.6},{"text":"Similarly, on the question whether there should be a full investigation, it is a matter of law we say.","start":4526.906,"stop":4538.451,"duration":11.55},{"text":"Four courts we've cited in the brief, four of the Circuits have said that you've got to have a full investigation on the record instead of the kind of investigation that was had here off the record with the trustee even turning down and objecting to us and blocking us when we wanted to get discovery of some of the most important facts here that we had found in third-party hands.","start":4538.451,"stop":4562.897,"duration":24.45},{"text":"Similarly, when we say that there must be a full disclosure of the basis of compromise, it is a fact that the compromise basis was not stated on the record and three more of the Circuit Courts which we've cited in the briefs have said this.","start":4562.897,"stop":4585.166,"duration":22.27},{"text":"It's our view that it's this Court's function and responsibility in response really to Justice Fortas' question as what we want here, to make it clear that the law is the same in the Fifth Circuit.","start":4585.166,"stop":4600.969,"duration":15.8},{"text":"And the law should be the same throughout the country so that we don't have the danger of what happens, what is traditionally happened.","start":4600.969,"stop":4609.937,"duration":8.97},{"text":"What caused Chapter X, people without any supervision, running bankruptcies to suit themselves, friendly trustees, private deals.","start":4609.937,"stop":4627.504,"duration":17.57},{"text":"Another thing that we think the Court must enunciate as a rule of law here is that the trustee must put under an affirmative duty to bring in to the record all the evidence that there's on valuation.","start":4627.504,"stop":4642.19,"duration":14.69},{"text":"Mr. Simmons, I'm sure inadvertently made a mistake -- meant there when he said, that our own expert, the committee's expert valued this property at only $4,500,000 as a going concern value.","start":4642.19,"stop":4659.922,"duration":17.73},{"text":"There is a passage in the record.","start":4659.922,"stop":4663.223,"duration":3.3},{"text":"I could quote it but I will cite it.","start":4663.223,"stop":4664.799,"duration":1.58},{"text":"We've also cited it on the brief at pages 246 to 248 of the record that we call Roman II here in which the thrust -- in which our officer says -- our -- I'm sorry.","start":4664.799,"stop":4682.688,"duration":17.89},{"text":"In which our expert says that the officers of the company, the trustee, have not furnished him with only information he needs to determine how much higher, how much higher than $4,500,000 it should be.","start":4682.688,"stop":4701.608,"duration":18.92},{"text":"Our expert did not make a valuation in terms of -- this is the figure, he said that this is the minimum figure and the reason I haven't been able to get a higher figure is because the trustee can't -- wouldn't furnish me the information that's necessary.","start":4701.608,"stop":4718.79,"duration":17.18},{"text":"That's in the record and I have discussed --","start":4718.79,"stop":4720.685,"duration":1.9}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":4720.685,"stop":4721.499,"duration":0.81}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"-- and placed into the brief a number of other passages in which the trustee withheld information from a -- certainly one thing must be done here by way of remedy.","start":4721.499,"stop":4735.496,"duration":14},{"text":"The trustee must be instructive.","start":4735.496,"stop":4737.682,"duration":2.19},{"text":"Any trustee must be instructed that it is his duty to supply all the information.","start":4737.682,"stop":4743.916,"duration":6.23},{"text":"Another thing that we need that doesn't require any statement, any controversy of a fact, fewer matter of law, that there must be a ruling and we think that that the ruling should be the one that is set out in the SEC's brief that defrauders' stockholders do have a right to claim as creditors.","start":4743.916,"stop":4766.192,"duration":22.28},{"text":"That question was never ventilated below in the Court of Appeals because of the fact that the District Judge erroneously held and we think this is again holding as a matter of law that we were barred from raising the question because of laches.","start":4766.192,"stop":4784.368,"duration":18.18},{"text":"We say --","start":4784.368,"stop":4784.998,"duration":0.63}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Because of what?","start":4784.998,"stop":4786.395,"duration":1.4}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Sir?","start":4786.395,"stop":4787.025,"duration":0.63}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Because of what?","start":4787.025,"stop":4787.924,"duration":0.9}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Of laches, that we were too late in filing our claim.","start":4787.924,"stop":4792.311,"duration":4.39},{"text":"We say on that point that laches under the doctrines of this Court, and we've cited the (Inaudible) case in our brief that laches is a question of fact and that the District Judge has no authority as a matter of law, not as a matter of fact, to make a finding that we were in laches until there'd been a hearing on that question determining what would the excuses for our delay, what were the consequences, who was hurt by our delay as well as did we in fact delay.","start":4792.311,"stop":4833.209,"duration":40.9},{"text":"This is not a matter of bickering over facts.","start":4833.209,"stop":4835.682,"duration":2.47},{"text":"This is a matter of acting on agreed facts, facts which are indisputable in the record.","start":4835.682,"stop":4843.678,"duration":8},{"text":"There must also be, we say, by way of remedy here, a real review under Section 221 (5) which requires the judge to look over the whole cause of the proceedings and determine before he approves the plan, before he confirms it rather, that there has been an independent trustee.","start":4843.678,"stop":4867.759,"duration":24.08},{"text":"This is not a fact question.","start":4867.759,"stop":4870.596,"duration":2.84},{"text":"We think we have developed the facts which demonstrate that this trustee had been acting under conflict of interest.","start":4870.596,"stop":4876.994,"duration":6.4},{"text":"The question is not whether he was corrupt but as this Court had said whether he had the opportunity for corruption and whether he had placed himself in a position where it can't be told, it can't be determined what he has done.","start":4876.994,"stop":4892.231,"duration":15.24},{"text":"It -- none of this is a question of fact.","start":4892.231,"stop":4895.44,"duration":3.21},{"text":"The trustee, we say, must go.","start":4895.44,"stop":4902.249,"duration":6.81},{"text":"It is not important really whether the trustee has the job as president of this company.","start":4902.249,"stop":4909.078,"duration":6.83},{"text":"What is important is that whether by a director's instruction in the mandate, unmistakable language in the opinion, it must be made plain that the plan must be vacated and that any other plan by a man who has acted in conflict of interest will also be vacated.","start":4909.078,"stop":4931.067,"duration":21.99},{"text":"This is a conclusion that we reached in our brief when we asked for relief.","start":4931.067,"stop":4935.23,"duration":4.16},{"text":"The SEC which has supported us throughout in this proceeding long before the particular questions that Mr. Ferber argued yesterday were raised.","start":4935.23,"stop":4945.085,"duration":9.86},{"text":"The SEC had reached the same conclusion and the conclusion of its -- stated in somewhat differentlanguage.","start":4945.085,"stop":4954.8,"duration":9.72},{"text":"It is our view that all of these things are things that the Court can do, the Court can order done in a mandate or indicate must be done in an opinion.","start":4954.8,"stop":4968.413,"duration":13.61},{"text":"That's what's necessary to claim this reorganization now.","start":4968.413,"stop":4977.578,"duration":9.17},{"text":"I would like to refer very briefly to some of Mr. Simmons' particular contentions that there was little dispute as to the amount of the Merrill-Stevens claim.","start":4977.578,"stop":4991.087,"duration":13.51},{"text":"There was a dispute as the amount of the Merrill-Stevens claim.","start":4991.087,"stop":4994.685,"duration":3.6},{"text":"The SEC objected to its allowance.","start":4994.685,"stop":4998.292,"duration":3.61},{"text":"At Roman II 1094 of the record that the SEC asked for a hearing on our particular objections to the Merrill-Stevens claim.","start":4998.292,"stop":5011.323,"duration":13.03},{"text":"It said that after those new specifications at large charging fraud were in the record that there must be a hearing on it.","start":5011.323,"stop":5020.657,"duration":9.33},{"text":"Finally, on this detailed points, it is important just to notice with respect to the suits, the objections to the various claims, the suits that were dropped, but what we're objecting to is that although each plan said that suits are reserved, all suits are reserved, all causes of action reserved that the trustee did not just make on the advise of his counsel that judgment of these were not worthy of prosecution, but that he made a deal not to prosecute them; that it was part of the deal and it was only disclosed in part three years later and another part four years later.","start":5020.657,"stop":5074.214,"duration":53.56},{"text":"This we say is no way to run a reorganization.","start":5074.214,"stop":5078.073,"duration":3.86}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that what you claim you could prove that you had a new (Inaudible)?","start":5078.073,"stop":5082.734,"duration":4.66}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, we think that that --","start":5082.734,"stop":5083.325,"duration":0.59}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":5083.325,"stop":5085.015,"duration":1.69}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"I think that passage of it, Your Honor, is already in the record.","start":5085.015,"stop":5089.619,"duration":4.6},{"text":"I know it's in the record.","start":5089.619,"stop":5090.721,"duration":1.1},{"text":"We've cited it in the record particularly in our reply brief when there was a contention that everything was disclosed at the Shaffer-Spitzer.","start":5090.721,"stop":5099.613,"duration":8.89},{"text":"We've cited the passages in the record in our reply brief.","start":5099.613,"stop":5104.081,"duration":4.47},{"text":"One final point on the law of the case, Mr. Simmons has made again I think in inadvertent statement which he said that the plan was returned at the time of the second appeal only, and I'm quoting him, for determination of its feasibility.","start":5104.081,"stop":5132.758,"duration":28.68},{"text":"He is I think quoting but the District Court said that it was returned only for determination of its feasibility.","start":5132.758,"stop":5145.235,"duration":12.48},{"text":"On the third appeal whether its contention was made that the law of the case covered everything and I quote from the third appeal 364 F.2d at 936, where the District Court said the decisions of the appellate court sent the plan of reorganization back only for determined feasibility of the plan.","start":5145.235,"stop":5172.993,"duration":27.76},{"text":"The Fifth Circuit said on the third appeal, We do not agree but hold that this Court's reversal of the order of confirmation left open those issues not in terms discussed and decided.","start":5172.993,"stop":5188.122,"duration":15.13},{"text":"The only issue that was discussed and decided with respect to us was the matter or decided against us was the prophylactic barring of the trustee.","start":5188.122,"stop":5201.416,"duration":13.29},{"text":"This is why we say that the Fifth Circuit did not exercise its supervisory function and why this Court has to step in and exercise its supervisory function because on each of the first two appeals where we had raised all almost of these questions, although the plans were set aside and this is important, perhaps I didn't make this clear in response to your question yesterday, Mr. Justice Harlan.","start":5201.416,"stop":5231.907,"duration":30.49},{"text":"On our first appeal of claim was set aside and our second appeal, the claim was set aside but they were set aside on collateral grounds which the Fifth Circuit did not find necessary to consider the particular questions that we had raised except by indirection where it said that the Court could act, the court below on the first appeal could act on the findings ofthe trustee had belatedly made with respect to the Shaffer-Spitzer and could set aside the first plan for fraud.","start":5231.907,"stop":5266.751,"duration":34.84},{"text":"This is the reason why we've brought the case here under the supervisory power primarily and this is the reason why we say that there can be a mandate and there can be instructions and there can be an opinion that without going into details bickerings about petty facts here, acting only on what is claimed in the record will clean up reorganization again.","start":5266.751,"stop":5303.106,"duration":36.35}]}]},{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - November 07, 1967","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren15/oral_argument_audio/15542","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":0,"stop":24.741,"duration":24.74}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court.","start":24.741,"stop":29.953,"duration":5.21},{"text":"This is corporate reorganization case arising under Chapter 10 of the Bankruptcy Act.","start":29.953,"stop":36.175,"duration":6.22},{"text":"It comes here from the Fifth Circuit and originated in the Southern District of Florida where the company under reorganization has its home port and principal office.","start":36.175,"stop":49.349,"duration":13.17},{"text":"It's in the business of supplying ocean shipping service of a specialized nature.","start":49.349,"stop":56.277,"duration":6.93},{"text":"It falls well or highway rather trailers overseas, the maritime equivalent of railroad fleet.","start":56.277,"stop":69.013,"duration":12.74},{"text":"The petitioner Protective Committee consists of a small group of small stockholders who hold authorizations from like stockholders, but they have attempted throughout 10 years in three reorganization plans involved here to discharge their responsibility to the whole group of public stockholders and not insofar as the record shows to over 7000 stockholders who hold over one million eight hundred thousand shares of stock which was sold to them in an original flotation or a series of flotations of stock of this company at prices up to $4.5 and $5 a share in a rig market for the most part in violation of the 1933 Securities Act, so far as registration is concerned and also in violation of various fraud provisions that would be applicable under both of 1933 and 1934 Act.","start":69.013,"stop":138.907,"duration":69.89},{"text":"The protective committee seeks to set aside this plan of reorganization, the third as I said which excluded the stockholders from participation in the reorganized company.","start":138.907,"stop":152.84,"duration":13.93},{"text":"They say that this reorganization is a rehearsal of the classic pattern of the reorganization scandals of generation ago that resulted in Chapter 10.","start":152.84,"stop":167.729,"duration":14.89},{"text":"Scattered innocent security holders are excluded from the reorganization which has been dominated we say by the people who wreck the old company and notwithstanding charges of mismanagement and fraud against them, they come out either with priorities or with control of the company.","start":167.729,"stop":194.93,"duration":27.2},{"text":"We served as Brown's proportion not a long Trail Court errors of law particularly in the area of Valuation Law and Securities Law but that there is a pervading failure on the part of both courts below to hold the trustee who in Chapter 10 is the key to a fair and honest reorganization to the performance of the statutory duties.","start":194.93,"stop":225.517,"duration":30.59},{"text":"We say that he performed belated and inadequate investigations particularly of charges of fraud against the people who ran the company and come out on top.","start":225.517,"stop":241.087,"duration":15.57},{"text":"We say that he made some errors of securities law which Mr. Ferber for the SEC proposed to discuss a little bit later, but we say that basically what was wrong was that both courts refused to hold the trustee to his duties of investigation, particularly of frauds of disclosure, particularly of compromises with people charged with fraud and in one instance established so far as the trustee himself is concerned by an investigation which he had made, which came up for the demonstration of fraud to his satisfaction on the basis of which he recommended for example that under the Taylor Triborough Doctrine those people should go to the bottom of the reorganization, but they came out on top.","start":241.087,"stop":290.76,"duration":49.67},{"text":"And we say that he failed to disclose the basis of his comprises with and after they had been charged with fraud which had never been recorded.","start":290.76,"stop":302.696,"duration":11.94},{"text":"He failed to bring into the record various facts which are of importance on valuation.","start":302.696,"stop":309.973,"duration":7.28},{"text":"He fudged we say, some of the valuation facts which were in the record and most important of all he failed in his basic duty for which the statute imposed upon him of independence.","start":309.973,"stop":326.91,"duration":16.94},{"text":"He had a fiduciary duty under the statute to stay it on the length with all the people in the reorganization and instead he entered into alliances with them.","start":326.91,"stop":340.697,"duration":13.79},{"text":"For example the largest single creditor whose case I shall discuss in a moment turned up on the Board of Directors with him and he himself on the Board of Directors, a fact which the SEC proposes to argue as having special significance.","start":340.697,"stop":364.176,"duration":23.48},{"text":"And we say that he had a duty to accept no favors at the hands of the people with whom he was required to deal and with whom he made these compromises.","start":364.176,"stop":380.645,"duration":16.47},{"text":"We say he violated these -- his duty by accepting his position as President of the new company at the hands of people charged with fraud and also at the hands of people who were discount claim buyers who were interested in patronage and they too sit on the Board with him now.","start":380.645,"stop":405.362,"duration":24.72},{"text":"Sir, this is the third time that the case has been up to the Court of Appeals and one of our complaints here, the reason that we presented the case under the supervisory power rather than just under conflicts is that we felt that the Court of Appeals has a share of the responsibility for happened here that on the first two appeals, on the first one we raised some of these points that we are now raising, on the second appeal we raised all of them, passed them off, didn't issue advisory guidance on these points, dismissed them as moot and thereby encouraged the court below to encourage the trustee it his dereliction of duty.","start":405.362,"stop":452.258,"duration":46.9},{"text":"And on the third one its plain from the opinion and the court said this case has been here nine years, as a matter of discretion we might just well let it go that the Court of Appeals is pretty well bored with it and never looked into it and this is why we brought it here as a matter of the supervisory power.","start":452.258,"stop":473.364,"duration":21.11},{"text":"In the first appeal it was our position and it was dismissed as moot.","start":473.364,"stop":480.479,"duration":7.12},{"text":"The second appeal and it was combined with another appeal in which the main question of setting aside the first plan for fraud was brought up on certiorari.","start":480.479,"stop":495.122,"duration":14.64},{"text":"The second appeal, we didn't bring certiorari although the government on a collateral point that is collateral presentation did.","start":495.122,"stop":503.204,"duration":8.08},{"text":"The third time around we brought certiorari because only then was it then squarely presented.","start":503.204,"stop":509.886,"duration":6.68}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":509.886,"stop":518.875,"duration":8.99}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"No sir.","start":518.875,"stop":521.054,"duration":2.18},{"text":"Well, I beg your pardon.","start":521.054,"stop":523.001,"duration":1.95},{"text":"It is quite true that certiorari was denied but it was not, it was not our committee who asked for it.","start":523.001,"stop":531.224,"duration":8.22},{"text":"In the first case Mr. Shaffer and Spitzer who filed the brief here filed for certiorari denied, in the second case the custody himself on a collateral question to the government priority rate, filed for certiorari also denied and the third time we brought it here.","start":531.224,"stop":547.678,"duration":16.45}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That was on the tax issue.","start":547.678,"stop":549.937,"duration":2.26}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes the priority, well really the priority of non-tax plan.","start":549.937,"stop":553.023,"duration":3.09}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":553.023,"stop":555.36,"duration":2.34}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, what I think illustrates what happened here and what we complain now first is the treatment of the claim of Merrill-Stevens Dry-dock and Repair Company, which is the shipyard that had the largest single creditor claim in the case.","start":555.36,"stop":577.885,"duration":22.52},{"text":"Merrill-Stevens claimed amount of about $1,600,000.","start":577.885,"stop":584.639,"duration":6.75},{"text":"Most of it was for conversation work on the company's self propelled vessel called the Carib Queen.","start":584.639,"stop":595.322,"duration":10.68},{"text":"What immediately provoked the reorganization was the fact that the Carib Queen on her maiden voyage to France had a boiler blowup and this crippled the Queen and the crippled the company and led to reorganization.","start":595.322,"stop":614.363,"duration":19.04},{"text":"Of course the validity of that claim just as a matter of a commercial claim was a better subject of dispute.","start":614.363,"stop":623.498,"duration":9.13},{"text":"When a boiler blows up and a vessel is put out of commission, so that the company has to limp along after that has it did during the reorganization with barges only, there is a lot of serious problem involved and this was at first disposed off by the trustee notwithstanding there was evidence that it was not alone the Queen that it had been subject to shoddy workmanship, but another vessel had capsized after having been designed by Merrill-Stevens, still another vessel had been put out of the shipyard with some defect in discharge line, which of course at the swamp and sink and there were all of these shall we say commercial defenses.","start":623.498,"stop":673.822,"duration":50.32},{"text":"The trustee recommended payment in full, after an off the record of investigation.","start":673.822,"stop":681.227,"duration":7.4},{"text":"The Security and Exchange Commission made its own investigation, purely on the question of what I might call a commercial claim.","start":681.227,"stop":690.353,"duration":9.13},{"text":"He came to the conclusion that there were defenses.","start":690.353,"stop":694.947,"duration":4.59},{"text":"They weren't perfect, but they should either be litigated out for if an appropriate settlement whose dimension that commission wasn't prepared the state within the week it should be settled out.","start":694.947,"stop":707.629,"duration":12.68},{"text":"We the committee were dissatisfied with that, just as we had been dissatisfied with some earlier refusals of the trustee to investigate.","start":707.629,"stop":716.717,"duration":9.09},{"text":"We obtained leave from the court to investigate and we made a further investigation, as a result of which we turned out charges and we outlined the evidence of fraud by Merrill-Stevens, its largest creditor.","start":716.717,"stop":733.621,"duration":16.9},{"text":"The essence of the fraud, the details I have to skim over consisted of participation in a fraud by other people in the case.","start":733.621,"stop":744.923,"duration":11.3},{"text":"The other people in the case are a group headed by a man named Abrams, a notorious stock swindler who was in Federal prison at the time of this reorganization, although not convicted of any matters involved in this company, a representative of a respectable security house, a man named Shaffer.","start":744.923,"stop":777.872,"duration":32.95},{"text":"The trustee in a belated investigation that wasted three years of this reorganization, the one that resulted in the first certiorari that Mr. Justice Harlan asked me about, had found that Abrams and Shaffer had wrecked this company, that there had been in the pre-reorganization stage a large number of sales of securities, most of them in violation of the Securities Act and fraudulent by virtue of the techniques that I have mentioned.","start":777.872,"stop":819.206,"duration":41.33},{"text":"And furthermore he had found notwithstanding denials by M/s. Shaffer and Spitzer and some of the people associated with them, that Shaffer and Spitzer who came into reorganization posing as innocent mortgagee title holders, actually knew that the beneficial interest in the mortgage that they have and which wound up with the priority were to a large extent owned by Shaffer and by Abrams, Directors of the records of the company but this was hidden.","start":819.206,"stop":856.597,"duration":37.39},{"text":"And this was the crime -- this was the matter that it had led to this first plan.","start":856.597,"stop":862.66,"duration":6.06},{"text":"The trustee refused to accept leads that we had offered him showing the connection and it wasn't until three years later as a result of an independent investigation by the SEC followed by a thorough so far as it went investigation on 167, the statute section that provides for formal investigation, full investigation that these things were discovered and at that time the trustee recommended that Shaffer's Spitzer should go to the bottom of the heap, that there should be suits pressed against them against the individuals behind them that there should be.","start":862.66,"stop":904.824,"duration":42.16}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"On behalf of the company?","start":904.824,"stop":906.318,"duration":1.49}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"On behalf of the company and also the point or one of the points that Mr. Faber proposed to discuss that the individual stockholders who had been defrauded by the company had a position to creditors just as if they have been run down by a company truck or had failed to receive goods.","start":906.318,"stop":923.97,"duration":17.65}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":923.97,"stop":929.326,"duration":5.36}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"He said the company had claims on the individual--","start":929.326,"stop":932.84,"duration":3.51}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"As a result if there was recovery the recovery would go into the assets of --","start":932.84,"stop":936.72,"duration":3.88}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Sure, he recommended the assertion of both sets of claims, the company claim against these people, the stockholder claim against these people and also he recommended that there should be an offset against this innocent appearing mortgage which was on the most crucial assets that the company had and which had been put by these people who wrecked the company.","start":936.72,"stop":967.546,"duration":30.83},{"text":"On these assets, on the eve of bankruptcy for the option to turn them all, again the stock that everything went well and with the stranglehold in case everything worked out to nothing as look to be the case at that time.","start":967.546,"stop":990.532,"duration":22.99},{"text":"Now, essentially what I have said a the Shaffer Spitzer group and it's first reorganization plan was a digression because my interest in it is to point out to the Court that there were charges of fraud against this group.","start":990.532,"stop":1009.251,"duration":18.72},{"text":"And that they had been established by the trustee on the record in the result of an investigation although belatedly.","start":1009.251,"stop":1017.864,"duration":8.61},{"text":"And we have said also in this further investigation that we had made that the Merrill-Stevens group allied themselves with this, stop pushing in this fraud because they too had connive with management and with the people who are dominating management and it's financial matters to commit a fraud upon the maritime administration and upon the public.","start":1017.864,"stop":1047.692,"duration":29.83},{"text":"Again without going into the detail of it because it has never been investigated in fact there happens not to be a formal denial of it on the record.","start":1047.692,"stop":1061.471,"duration":13.78},{"text":"A portion of the stock portion was achieved in this case by representation as to a maritime commission guarantee on the construction mortgage of the Carib Queen in her reconversion of the company's use.","start":1061.471,"stop":1080.13,"duration":18.66},{"text":"The mortgage had been guaranteed by the maritime commission, which made a statutory finding which was much advertised by the stock pushers that the enterprise was economically sound and that guarantee could not have issued nor that representation had been made use of in the sales or not for fraud practices upon the maritime administration by a mortgaging out procedure.","start":1080.13,"stop":1109.077,"duration":28.95},{"text":"The statue under which the maritime administration operates initially in these loan guarantees requires that a certain fraction of the cost to be paid in cash, it was not.","start":1109.077,"stop":1121.147,"duration":12.07},{"text":"Although it was paid in cash, there was a hidden under-the-table deal whereby the cash would return right back to the company in exchange for company stock at an arbitrary price.","start":1121.147,"stop":1134.21,"duration":13.06},{"text":"The company was at the time putting stock down on the markets who, the hands of its friends and people who controlled it for all sorts of prices and for nothing.","start":1134.21,"stop":1144.844,"duration":10.63},{"text":"So this was way in which we said that there had been a fraud on the part of this major creditor.","start":1144.844,"stop":1154.443,"duration":9.6},{"text":"Now with respect to both these creditors the mortgagee group and the trustee had found guilty of fraud and the shipyard when we had alleged in detail although there had been no formal investigation was guilty of fraud nothing happened so far as the trustee was concerned by way of action on that fraud.","start":1154.443,"stop":1182.451,"duration":28.01},{"text":"Indeed at one point in support of our charges of fraud against Merrill-Stevens we attempted to bring into the record by ordinary discovery procedures, motion to produce and so on some documents bearing on it which we described after we located them that the trustee said he didn't know anything about it, he hadn't found them and the trustee opposed our attempt to obtain them by ordinary discovery procedures.","start":1182.451,"stop":1213.512,"duration":31.06}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Langbein, how is the state point which you are asking this Court to decide?","start":1213.512,"stop":1220.077,"duration":6.57}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"I would like the Court to rule as follows.","start":1220.077,"stop":1225.403,"duration":5.33}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Yeah go ahead.","start":1225.403,"stop":1229.096,"duration":3.69}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"First that a reorganization conducted by a trustee in disregard of his responsibilities to investigate and his responsibilities to disclose results in a reorganization plan which has to be set aside because the trustee's functions under the statute are too important to trifle with.","start":1229.096,"stop":1254.123,"duration":25.03}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Well I see there is no dispute as to that proposition of law.","start":1254.123,"stop":1257.663,"duration":3.54},{"text":"The question is how to try in this case?","start":1257.663,"stop":1262.976,"duration":5.31},{"text":"Is there any dispute as to that proposition of law?","start":1262.976,"stop":1267.482,"duration":4.51}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"I think there is some bickering about it in the briefs.","start":1267.482,"stop":1270.959,"duration":3.48}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Alright.","start":1270.959,"stop":1271.979,"duration":1.02}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"I regard it as myself substantially settled because I can find the counsel has not been able to cite any cases to the contrary.","start":1271.979,"stop":1280.825,"duration":8.85},{"text":"Next we would like to have the Court rule on the disqualifications of the trustee through making alliances with people whom he ought to kept at arm's length and because Section 221(5) of the Act requires that as a precondition of confirming a plan that the Court must take a look back over what's happened in the reorganization and satisfy itself of the independence of the trustee that the plan is bad if the trustee isn't independent.","start":1280.825,"stop":1310.981,"duration":30.16}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"I thought you also relied on the fact on [Inaudible] mentioning with that trustee [Inaudible]","start":1310.981,"stop":1321.676,"duration":10.69}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Yeah.","start":1321.676,"stop":1321.944,"duration":0.27}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"That trustee became the president on the of the reorganized company?","start":1321.944,"stop":1327.29,"duration":5.35}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes and the SEC was running this on the ground of prophylactic rule that no matter of what the facts the trustee has no business being president of the company, the way there has been a disputed reorganization plan, we say that while we agree with that position perhaps because we are closer to the facts.","start":1327.29,"stop":1345.248,"duration":17.96},{"text":"We don't have this magisterial view that the SEC has that on the particular facts the trustee disqualified himself because he made alliances with the people that he was supposed to create fiduciary in fashion and not make alliances with them, not get any conflict of interest.","start":1345.248,"stop":1360.948,"duration":15.7}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":1360.948,"stop":1363.585,"duration":2.64}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":1363.585,"stop":1368.279,"duration":4.69}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"One contention was ruled on against us by the Court of Appeals.","start":1368.279,"stop":1372.737,"duration":4.46},{"text":"This is what I call a prophylactic rule.","start":1372.737,"stop":1374.948,"duration":2.21},{"text":"The Court of Appeals expressly left open the question of whether a lack of independence in fact was available to us.","start":1374.948,"stop":1388.52,"duration":13.57},{"text":"It said that if we prove that it was in -- that he didn't have independence in fact that at that point we would have a bad point.","start":1388.52,"stop":1402.06,"duration":13.54},{"text":"I think this is --","start":1402.06,"stop":1402.346,"duration":0.29}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"We are asked to look at the record here and determine that the trustee was derelict in his fiduciary duty in the respect which you have been discussing and on that basis to confirm that the reorganization plans should be set aside?","start":1402.346,"stop":1422.781,"duration":20.43}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes well, there are other grounds that I'll come to in a moment Mr. Justice.","start":1422.781,"stop":1427.996,"duration":5.22},{"text":"We are asking you to look at the record.","start":1427.996,"stop":1431.896,"duration":3.9},{"text":"We have summarized the record and while there is dispute I think on some of the fringes of the fact, there is no dispute I think as to the main fact here, although I was somewhat surprised by, in the reply briefs and kind of a general denial and --","start":1431.896,"stop":1449.817,"duration":17.92}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Kind of a [Inaudible]","start":1449.817,"stop":1453.065,"duration":3.25}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Well it's vigorously general sir.","start":1453.065,"stop":1455.654,"duration":2.59}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"On which line I gather that we should agree with the SEC that it should be a prophylactic rule [Inaudible]","start":1455.654,"stop":1472.549,"duration":16.89}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir, I think so, but there are lot of things that need diagnose here and -","start":1472.549,"stop":1477.692,"duration":5.14}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well I  but suppose there was a conclusion that a prophylactic in the these circumstances is indicative?","start":1477.692,"stop":1486.638,"duration":8.95}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1486.638,"stop":1487.965,"duration":1.33}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That will be a general application, would that have the affect to setting aside this plan?","start":1487.965,"stop":1493.901,"duration":5.94}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"We think so.","start":1493.901,"stop":1494.842,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well if it did then why should we be concerning with all the other things?","start":1494.842,"stop":1498.753,"duration":3.91}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Well there are multiple grounds upon which we advance this case.","start":1498.753,"stop":1502.414,"duration":3.66},{"text":"One ground I haven't even mentioned except as a rubric the fact the district court announced and allowed the application of what we consider to be a rule of valuation law that is utterly contrary to every case that this Court has had on the subject.","start":1502.414,"stop":1521.31,"duration":18.9}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"On this issues that you are speaking that you've addressed yourself so far?","start":1521.31,"stop":1525.019,"duration":3.71}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes Your Honor.","start":1525.019,"stop":1527.365,"duration":2.35}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Necessarily to be getting into the record and all these matters and in fact the proper rule of law is a prophylactic rule?","start":1527.365,"stop":1537.021,"duration":9.66}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"If you can disclose it short by the prophylactic rule and if it follows from that as we say that the plan itself is bad if the trustee is independent then the plan goes back, but what I am afraid of, very much afraid of in view of the history of what happens when there is no affiliate guidance in this case that we are in for more of the same.","start":1537.021,"stop":1560.256,"duration":23.24},{"text":"We've had 10 years of this litigation.","start":1560.256,"stop":1562.475,"duration":2.22}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well it seems to me that the only prophylactic rule is urging that the trustee is not going to be trustee of the company and that's been set aside plan that [Inaudible] president of the company but it's otherwise make the plan exactly as it was?","start":1562.475,"stop":1582.455,"duration":19.98}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"No Your Honor we insist that the trustees' conflict of interest.","start":1582.455,"stop":1585.792,"duration":3.34}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"I know you do but it's the only that's wrong with the plan, is that the trustee is the president of the company, where you can get a new President of the company.","start":1585.792,"stop":1595.386,"duration":9.59}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Now we say that there are other things wrong with the plan.","start":1595.386,"stop":1597.578,"duration":2.19}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Exactly that's the answer to this, that's just credit isn't it, but there are other things wrong with this plan that must be cured.","start":1597.578,"stop":1605.197,"duration":7.62},{"text":"You say that trustee would not only become president of the company but in the process of compromising certain claims that there wasn't enough done to later comprise on and that the Court had also in approving the compromise.","start":1605.197,"stop":1618.331,"duration":13.13}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Right, sir.","start":1618.331,"stop":1619.208,"duration":0.88},{"text":"So that I think if you would nearly disposed off the thing on the basis of a finding that the trustee shouldn't become president, that wouldn't answer case.","start":1619.208,"stop":1630.446,"duration":11.24},{"text":"It's our view that what the trustee did on the way to becoming president compromised the whole record, made it impossible for one to make a fair determination as for example the facts that he put into the record on valuation.","start":1630.446,"stop":1646.628,"duration":16.18}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't know why -- did you ever object to, did you client ever object to trustee being president [Inaudible]","start":1646.628,"stop":1653.975,"duration":7.35}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh!","start":1653.975,"stop":1654.08,"duration":0.11},{"text":"Yes we did sir.","start":1654.08,"stop":1656.937,"duration":2.86},{"text":"Not on the first plan, although he was President in the first plan too, but in the second plan and in the third plan we objected and in the proceedings below we objected.","start":1656.937,"stop":1667.118,"duration":10.18}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"There are proceedings available in reorganization [Inaudible] trustee on that?","start":1667.118,"stop":1672.796,"duration":5.68}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"It happens that that there are no precedents on the subject and I need --","start":1672.796,"stop":1677.284,"duration":4.49}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":1677.284,"stop":1680.668,"duration":3.38}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"I am certain that there are procedures available although the statute doesn't spell them out ","start":1680.668,"stop":1684.967,"duration":4.3}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Nobody trust, nobody trust [Inaudible]","start":1684.967,"stop":1686.975,"duration":2.01}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"It would be too outrageous if one didn't have that, but we did not make any attempt to remove the trustee by an independent procedure.","start":1686.975,"stop":1698.313,"duration":11.34},{"text":"The reason for it is that there is a claim remedy available for an non-independent trustee knock out the plan and as a core committee we even had to have the court under the old rules weigh depending on the record, we couldn't afford to go up on every side skirmish.","start":1698.313,"stop":1716.073,"duration":17.76},{"text":"Most of the trustee's lack of independence was built up during the proceedings that lasted very few months in the formulation of the second plan.","start":1716.073,"stop":1725.642,"duration":9.57},{"text":"It was at that time that we began to realize that the trustee was withholding evidence from the record, that the trustee was making alliances with people with whom we thought he shouldn't make alliances that he was granting sweetheart contracts for example to one of these claim buyer that cost the company a $100,000 a year over the nearest competitive bid that he was running off people majors in the industry I am talking about the towing contract, majors in the industry whom we brought in and whom he refused to allow to have information that he was running off bidders whom we proposed to bring in because he wouldn't give them information that he was rejecting a cash plan which was offered by an alternative bidder whom we didn't bring in to the case.","start":1725.642,"stop":1781.3,"duration":55.66}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":1781.3,"stop":1783.922,"duration":2.62}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir they are.","start":1783.922,"stop":1786.37,"duration":2.45}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":1786.37,"stop":1791.276,"duration":4.91}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"To the extent that they are un-denied we -","start":1791.276,"stop":1793.913,"duration":2.64}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":1793.913,"stop":1798.676,"duration":4.76}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Not solely Your Honor, to the extent that they are un-denied in the record.","start":1798.676,"stop":1802.925,"duration":4.25},{"text":"This is not the kind of a case that the Court doesn't go into such as resolving disputes of fact that have been resolved by the judge.","start":1802.925,"stop":1812.494,"duration":9.57},{"text":"But I think the mere fact that somebody in a brief says that where we say we charge fraud against Merrill-Stevens and one of the answering brief says no, they never charged fraud against Merrill-Stevens, that's merely cited on the brief, shouldn't preclude the Court from what is unpleasant and difficult duty most of which probably does get turned over to the Courts, going to the record and finding out whether what we say is so.","start":1812.494,"stop":1846.203,"duration":33.71},{"text":"This occurs anytime that there is a fundamental miscarriage of Trial Court justice.","start":1846.203,"stop":1856.041,"duration":9.84}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":1856.041,"stop":1862.521,"duration":6.48}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes I think we can sir.","start":1862.521,"stop":1864.673,"duration":2.15},{"text":"We think that this was a primary duty of the Court of Appeals that when we said these very things to the Court of Appeals with chapter and verse citation to this record that it was the Court of Appeals' duty not to flip this off as it did saying well this is a matter of discretion.","start":1864.673,"stop":1880.888,"duration":16.21},{"text":"But when we say that the record is poisoned, they may have taken a look at the record, but what they did was to say that this is a matter of discretion and when we said that the trustee derelictions of duty were compounded by errors of law on the part of the Trial Court, for example in enunciating a wrong rule of evaluation law and when we say that the trustee prevented us from having a true evaluation of the proper number of claims, that at that point this passes beyond the boundary of discretion.","start":1880.888,"stop":1921.042,"duration":40.15},{"text":"We are no longer dealing with something, the Court has the evidence before and it ruled as it -- as it had the right to rule on disputed questions of fact.","start":1921.042,"stop":1932.438,"duration":11.4},{"text":"This not discretion.","start":1932.438,"stop":1934.31,"duration":1.87},{"text":"This is error of law particularly in the area where we say -- particularly in the area where we say that the trustee who has the duty of making up a record for the Court distorted the record.","start":1934.31,"stop":1952.102,"duration":17.79},{"text":"The Court didn't pass on those issues in fact.","start":1952.102,"stop":1954.968,"duration":2.87},{"text":"These are very serious charges.","start":1954.968,"stop":1956.713,"duration":1.74},{"text":"They go the essence of bankruptcy as --","start":1956.713,"stop":1960.676,"duration":3.96}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Why do you on the claims, why do you need to go beyond just saying that there is no, not sufficient places in the record for these compromises?","start":1960.676,"stop":1969.647,"duration":8.97}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"That is one ground that we certainly have --","start":1969.647,"stop":1971.108,"duration":1.46}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"But you don't need to get these other charges of alliances and fraud, do you?","start":1971.108,"stop":1976.738,"duration":5.63}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"Well not just to knock out those --","start":1976.738,"stop":1979.39,"duration":2.65}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"If all the record showed that the trustee walks in the Court that here are some claims which have been objected to, but I recommend they be compromised at X dollars and the Court said fine, X dollars.","start":1979.39,"stop":1990.308,"duration":10.92},{"text":"Your position is that just about all that happened and it's insufficient.","start":1990.308,"stop":1994.212,"duration":3.9}]},{"speakerName":"Irwin L. Langbein","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":1994.212,"stop":1997.275,"duration":3.06},{"text":"We think the case law says that and likewise we say that on the other major issues here valuation and wrong standard.","start":1997.275,"stop":2003.703,"duration":6.43},{"text":"Valuation -- wrong standard, that's a matter of law and when the trustee acting under that wrong standard doesn't bring into the record or the Court keeps out of the record evidence for example of the present trends of the company, where he allows the company to be valued on the basis of three ships, although in fact there are four now, where he allows the company to valued on the basis of barges although the trustee has well matured plans.","start":2003.703,"stop":2035.909,"duration":32.21},{"text":"He's been spending company money, going out and investigating another type of ship, which he says is going to make it cheaper to run.","start":2035.909,"stop":2049.936,"duration":14.03},{"text":"That at that point that evidence has got to come into the record and the Trial Judge said, no it can't come into the record.","start":2049.936,"stop":2057.699,"duration":7.76},{"text":"I'm not interested in anything expect what's happening now.","start":2057.699,"stop":2063.085,"duration":5.39},{"text":"This is a type of thing that we say you have to go beyond in order to stop this from happening again.","start":2063.085,"stop":2069.621,"duration":6.54},{"text":"That this [Inaudible] is one of these fields and reorganization is one of these fields, it just requires supervision every now and then.","start":2069.621,"stop":2076.533,"duration":6.91},{"text":"This is what makes bankruptcy ring.","start":2076.533,"stop":2078.857,"duration":2.32},{"text":"We say to the Court to look into these things in every once in a while I am reminded of the right to consultation from the days of [Inaudible] Julian Wayneright.","start":2078.857,"stop":2092.723,"duration":13.87},{"text":"He would bring them up here and we'd come up with charges and the Court would have to look into the record and see what happened.","start":2092.723,"stop":2100.082,"duration":7.36},{"text":"Unpleasant job, unpleasant to all of you, unpleasant to investigate.","start":2100.082,"stop":2105.981,"duration":5.9},{"text":"But if the Court of Appeals doesn't do it, we are committed to do the duty of this Court's [Inaudible] and the jury as well.","start":2105.981,"stop":2117.35,"duration":11.37}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":2117.35,"stop":2119.833,"duration":2.48}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, may it please the Court.","start":2119.833,"stop":2125.275,"duration":5.44},{"text":"I should like to first discuss the question of the trustee succeeding himself as the President of the reorganized company. Chapter 10 of the Bankruptcy Act provides that the choice of the person to head up the reorganized corporation must be Consistent with public policy.","start":2125.275,"stop":2149.737,"duration":24.46},{"text":"This is Section 221 of the Act which we quote on page four of our brief, if I may just read the applicable provision.","start":2149.737,"stop":2158.321,"duration":8.58},{"text":"The judge shall confirm a plan if satisfied that there are various requirements such as if the plan is fair and equitable and feasible and finally the last requirement is that the identity, qualifications and affiliations of the persons who are to be Directors or officers or voting trustees of any, upon the consummation of the plan have been fully disclosed and that the appointment of such persons to such offices or their continuance therein is equitable, compatible with the interests of the creditors and stockholders and consistent with public policy.","start":2158.321,"stop":2202.27,"duration":43.95},{"text":"Now, the choice of the reorganization trustee to be President of the reorganized company in our view flies directly in the face of policy of Chapter 10 which requires that the trustee be disinterested, Section 156 of the Act specifically provides that the trustee as well as counsel for the trustee must be disinterested and this is defined in Section 158 of the Act, disinterested.","start":2202.27,"stop":2238.237,"duration":35.97},{"text":"It excludes specific persons such as creditors and the debtor, stockholders and the debtor, the underwriter of existing securities of the debtor, Directors, officers and employees of the debtor and there is a catch-all at the end and this too is on page four of our brief.","start":2238.237,"stop":2257.442,"duration":19.2},{"text":"The final provision which says that a person shall not be deemed disinterested if it appears that he has by reason of any other direct or indirect relation to -- relationship to, connection with or interest in the debtor or such underwriter or for any reason an interest materially adverse to interests of any class or stockholders.","start":2257.442,"stop":2285.407,"duration":27.97},{"text":"Now the importance --","start":2285.407,"stop":2287.879,"duration":2.47}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":2287.879,"stop":2308.768,"duration":20.89}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"We feel that unless --","start":2308.768,"stop":2310.198,"duration":1.43}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":2310.198,"stop":2310.904,"duration":0.71}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes we feel that --","start":2310.904,"stop":2312.586,"duration":1.68}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":2312.586,"stop":2315.692,"duration":3.11}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"No Your Honor, there have been fairly few cases where this has come up.","start":2315.692,"stop":2323.687,"duration":7.99},{"text":"We have urged the position in several district court cases, the SEC as you may know although a party to these reorganizations may not take appeals.","start":2323.687,"stop":2335.762,"duration":12.08}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":2335.762,"stop":2342.161,"duration":6.4}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"So far as I am aware we have that position in various cases going back at least to the 40s.","start":2342.161,"stop":2349.335,"duration":7.17},{"text":"I believe there were cases in the earlier days where the commission may not have taken that position and there may have been -- I just haven't had -- been able to survey them all, there may have some cases more recently where we neglected to.","start":2349.335,"stop":2366.201,"duration":16.87}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"In certain organizations, the SEC is obligated to the write a report on the plan?","start":2366.201,"stop":2370.517,"duration":4.32}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes Your Honor.","start":2370.517,"stop":2371.469,"duration":0.95}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"And did you say you don't recall any cases since the early 1940s in which you have not objected to the trustee becoming President of a company of reorganization?","start":2371.469,"stop":2382.597,"duration":11.13}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't recall any, but there could have been some.","start":2382.597,"stop":2385.369,"duration":2.77},{"text":"I just -- in other words I only know appeal cases where this has occurred in recent years and at least in the last few years those cases where it occurred, we did object.","start":2385.369,"stop":2396.577,"duration":11.21}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Did you take the position having objected and the trustee having nevertheless appointment President of the new company, did you take position of that invalidates the plan?","start":2396.577,"stop":2407.984,"duration":11.41}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, that was the -- this was the place we took the position in, in connection with objecting to the approval of a plan if the approval show that the trustee was to be as occurred in I believe in this case and otherwise at the confirmation.","start":2407.984,"stop":2421.948,"duration":13.96}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that's place that you have failed to expose your [Inaudible] you assert that position, but suppose your position were disallowed, did you thereafter take the position that invalidated the plan and made any distinction between the time and the occasion of which you make your objection and the consequences of the disallowance of your objection.","start":2421.948,"stop":2447.53,"duration":25.58},{"text":"Because here you are saying not merely that it was wrong for the court below to approve the plan, to approve that feature of the plan, the trustee as a President, but you are saying that, that such approval invalidate the plan in this ground for setting aside?","start":2447.53,"stop":2469.348,"duration":21.82}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, the confirmation of the plan we are saying and this where we generally would object in another words when the plan was submitted to us or when we first learned that it was contemplated that the Chapter 10 trustee was to be the President of -- now this often we come up very, very late in the proceeding of course.","start":2469.348,"stop":2490.963,"duration":21.62},{"text":"Now the reason that we feel that this is important and believe me we too have, we've learned from experience and that's why I think our past action should not certainly conclude as here.","start":2490.963,"stop":2502.991,"duration":12.03},{"text":"We think that when we look at the importance of the requirement of the disinterested trustee, which was certainly emphasized by the legislative history, the studies that preceded the adoption of Chapter 10 had shown case after case, where those able to manipulate the reorganization proceeding had benefited of the expenses scattered public investors to a lack of an independent trustee.","start":2502.991,"stop":2532.762,"duration":29.77},{"text":"The committee report, the house report noted that the functions of the independent trustee appointed in the larger cases are difficult to over emphasize and I continue, only through an impartial trustee can the court be in a position to exercise an informed judgment and to afford a critical scrutiny and supervision of these state at all times.","start":2532.762,"stop":2562.918,"duration":30.16},{"text":"The commission's representative testified that the reorganization trustee, that requirement that he be disinterested was the key to real reform.","start":2562.918,"stop":2573.754,"duration":10.84}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"That was the reform that the, a basic reform that the statute put in by requiring a disinterested trustee.","start":2573.754,"stop":2580.549,"duration":6.8}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Exactly.","start":2580.549,"stop":2581.767,"duration":1.22}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"And if you have a disinterested trustee, truly so meeting all the requirements to the letter in the statute then what's wrong with such a very high minded disinterested person becoming President of a reorganized corporation?","start":2581.767,"stop":2596.445,"duration":14.68}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"It is our position that a man cannot continue to be disinterested once he is angling for the job of becoming President of the reorganized corporation.","start":2596.445,"stop":2608.183,"duration":11.74},{"text":"We don't know the moment he cease to be disinterested, but we do know that somewhere along the line he has been having conversations.","start":2608.183,"stop":2616.692,"duration":8.51},{"text":"He has been talking with people.","start":2616.692,"stop":2618.927,"duration":2.24},{"text":"He may have been taking actions to bring about this result and it is our position that there is a clear conflict of interest between wanting the fairest and best plan for security holders and wanting a plan that will make you the President of the reorganized company.","start":2618.927,"stop":2635.515,"duration":16.59}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Suppose he fell from grace only after the all the other terms of the plan had been approved, suppose this paragon and all these trustees are supposed to be paragons of virtue and suppose this paragon continue to be a paragon that everything else was decided and then he was invited to neighborhood salon by the dominant merging interest in the company and they discuss the matter quietly and they reluctantly agree that he would become President of the company. Does that make any difference in the absoluteness of the SEC's view?","start":2635.515,"stop":2678.178,"duration":42.66}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't believe so because I think the difficulty of proof of such thing just impossible.","start":2678.178,"stop":2686.294,"duration":8.12},{"text":"For the outsider to be able to disprove that this is the way it happened.","start":2686.294,"stop":2691.305,"duration":5.01},{"text":"Now in this case it epitomizes the contracts, I mean the conflict that the trustee was confronted with whether or not he was an honest man.","start":2691.305,"stop":2705.499,"duration":14.19},{"text":"Whether or not in other words, let's assume that he was completely honest.","start":2705.499,"stop":2713.265,"duration":7.77},{"text":"He had choices to make, which a man cannot make without serious conflict that's, we think ceases to make disinterested.","start":2713.265,"stop":2725.193,"duration":11.93},{"text":"For example the charge here that in the operation of the business he signed a sweetheart contract with a Florida Towing Company.","start":2725.193,"stop":2736.803,"duration":11.61},{"text":"This was a contract $1,500,000 a year, the biggest expense of the company.","start":2736.803,"stop":2744.031,"duration":7.23},{"text":"It's charged by the committee that he could have gotten the same kind of contract for $100,000 less, I don't know whether that so or not, but we do know that Florida Towing Corporation has a man on the Board of Directors and was a very substantial creditor at the top.","start":2744.031,"stop":2762.144,"duration":18.11},{"text":"So that here was a conflict right in the operation of the business of not hurting or perhaps helping someone which you would want to vote for you to be the President of the reorganized company.","start":2762.144,"stop":2774.673,"duration":12.53},{"text":"The --","start":2774.673,"stop":2775.312,"duration":0.64}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"I suppose you realize what you are arguing for is -- goes against agreement of various fashionable practices --","start":2775.312,"stop":2786.897,"duration":11.59}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't know the instances to which you are referring --","start":2786.897,"stop":2788.514,"duration":1.62}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"Well I just happened to think if we galaxy of former Generals and what not who head up the big corporations of America who had served the Pentagon in [Inaudible] positions.","start":2788.514,"stop":2803.339,"duration":14.82}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe Your Honor that at least for several years.","start":2803.339,"stop":2807.696,"duration":4.36}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"I am not trying to defend them I am just saying that [Laughter] perhaps you are talking about a symptom of a disease that's much broader in this Chapter 10?","start":2807.696,"stop":2818.061,"duration":10.37}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I think at least there are some safeguard in that area.","start":2818.061,"stop":2821.512,"duration":3.45},{"text":"I believe for example the general who goes with the Chairman of the Board the new corporation cannot appear before the Defense Department at least for several years or with respect to any matter as to which he had worked previously.","start":2821.512,"stop":2835.324,"duration":13.81},{"text":"So at least there are some sorts of safeguards, but here I think that the disinterested and this is not just in lacking because of the operations of course, but even more basically because of his duties in bringing about a fair plan in compromising claims.","start":2835.324,"stop":2856.366,"duration":21.04},{"text":"For example the compromises here, we don't say that you have to determine on this record that the compromises were unfair.","start":2856.366,"stop":2865.955,"duration":9.59},{"text":"We think that you can determine very easily from this record that the compromises were not sufficiently explained that the compromise of Merrill-Stevens claim whereby Merrill-Stevens who received 40% of the stock of the debtor whereby they got their entire claim paid in full with an explanation of about one paragraph which in effect said something about well we don't think they would take less.","start":2865.955,"stop":2893.987,"duration":28.03}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"Were these compromises, does a record show that these compromises were made after the trustee was approached with respect of becoming President of the company?","start":2893.987,"stop":2905.994,"duration":12.01}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"We don't know when the trustee was approached.","start":2905.994,"stop":2908.018,"duration":2.02},{"text":"We don't know when this began Justice Fortas and this is one of the things we do know.","start":2908.018,"stop":2912.034,"duration":4.02}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"There are lots of temptations to which even an independent trustee [Inaudible] for example on the questions of abuse, trustees would know for example that this case in these two companies to which you refer, would have a lot to say about whether he gets a $100,000 or $500,000 as fees?","start":2912.034,"stop":2936.061,"duration":24.03}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Only when he is, when its out of  you mean trustee fees?","start":2936.061,"stop":2937.807,"duration":1.75}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"What you are saying maybe perfectly valid moral point that is to say that because of the difficulty of knowing just when trustee agreed to become a President or when came the idea and also because there is a prospect that he might become President of the company, he might make unduly favorable settlements if the people who were merged with control, it maybe correct or moral idea, but when you say that should be a principle of law assisted on by this Court rather than something that Congress to legislate here I suppose is a very serious problem.","start":2937.807,"stop":2983.923,"duration":46.12}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"It's the serious problem.","start":2983.923,"stop":2985.192,"duration":1.27},{"text":"The Congress did legislate and said that the trustee must be disinterested.","start":2985.192,"stop":2989.434,"duration":4.24},{"text":"It seems to me that that means this be in a position where he does not have serious conflicts of interests among the service of the trust in effect the security holders when he is to make the plans when its up to --","start":2989.434,"stop":3006.83,"duration":17.4}]},{"speakerName":"Abe Fortas","textObjs":[{"text":"You're saying that you got to do some fairly rough at least arbitrary things with respect to time.","start":3006.83,"stop":3019.696,"duration":12.87},{"text":"Now when the man that's presumably when this man was appointed as trustee was independent then he later fell from grace?","start":3019.696,"stop":3030.188,"duration":10.49}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"If this prophylactic position that we are asserting is followed it will prevent such falls from grace.","start":3030.188,"stop":3038.138,"duration":7.95},{"text":"I didn't, haven't had a chance to point out the many important procedures that the trustee must accomplish.","start":3038.138,"stop":3050.535,"duration":12.4},{"text":"He is the one who is primarily in charge of putting together the reorganization plan and valuing the debt and of taking positions as to what claims he shall oppose and of taking positions between perhaps contesting plans in each of these areas.","start":3050.535,"stop":3068.282,"duration":17.75},{"text":"In this very case the trustee was put into serious positions of conflict.","start":3068.282,"stop":3072.745,"duration":4.46},{"text":"For example, in the early plan which went through very quickly when the trustee skipped evaluation hearing and did not even begin to investigate this Caplan mortgage claim and the Caplan people got control of the reorganized company and he was made President.","start":3072.745,"stop":3094.402,"duration":21.66},{"text":"Now, assuming he had a deal with those people to be President now naturally his interest was not to delay the reorganization by going through all these procedures.","start":3094.402,"stop":3107.695,"duration":13.29},{"text":"With respect to the stockholders here, they have been litigating with the trustee.","start":3107.695,"stop":3114.373,"duration":6.68},{"text":"They've been making all sorts of charges against him.","start":3114.373,"stop":3117.095,"duration":2.72},{"text":"Presumably if they were cut into this reorganization, they would not be tempted to vote for him to be its President.","start":3117.095,"stop":3124.304,"duration":7.21},{"text":"And so that when he is undervaluing, if he is undervaluing the data which will cut the stockholders out, here perhaps he didn't undervalue, but it certainly there was a conflict.","start":3124.304,"stop":3137.243,"duration":12.94},{"text":"Similarly when he opposed the claims of these stockholders, the creditor claims that is the base -- the in effect recession claims on the theory that they purchased them on the ground of fraud when he opposed it not only on the merits but procedurally because he claimed the claims were filed, well he may have been right but he was certainly in the conflicting position to do this.","start":3137.243,"stop":3159.594,"duration":22.35}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":3159.594,"stop":3168.97,"duration":9.38}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"I am not representing Your Honor that the trustee in these areas consciously violated his trust.","start":3168.97,"stop":3177.578,"duration":8.61},{"text":"I do think he was derelict in his duties in not having the kind of hearings that the act contemplates in making compromises without bringing them out into the open and then not affording the procedures which Chapter X requires.","start":3177.578,"stop":3193.694,"duration":16.12}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":3193.694,"stop":3199.539,"duration":5.85}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":3199.539,"stop":3201.428,"duration":1.89}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":3201.428,"stop":3205.979,"duration":4.55}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Three and this -- and compromised.","start":3205.979,"stop":3211.56,"duration":5.58},{"text":"I really don't know Your Honor, there were never a panel of more than three.","start":3211.56,"stop":3218.039,"duration":6.48},{"text":"I should correct perhaps --","start":3218.039,"stop":3220.737,"duration":2.7}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":3220.737,"stop":3222.135,"duration":1.4}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"No, I should correct a misunderstanding I think that Mr. Langbein did misunderstand your earlier question, there were three appeals that his committee was in right at the beginning of the reorganization.","start":3222.135,"stop":3234.051,"duration":11.92},{"text":"There had been two other appeals by the Caplan group attempting to let it stay.","start":3234.051,"stop":3240.819,"duration":6.77},{"text":"So coming back but those first two appeals didn't delay this proceeding if anything they probably hastened it along because it was refusing to let them foreclose on the mortgage.","start":3240.819,"stop":3253.911,"duration":13.09},{"text":"My time is almost up.","start":3253.911,"stop":3258.347,"duration":4.44},{"text":"I think I'll have to rely on our briefs for our other points.","start":3258.347,"stop":3265.866,"duration":7.52},{"text":"I would like merely to conclude by saying that we think in this case that they were omitted a substantial number of the safeguards for the protection of the public that Chapter X was designed to provide.","start":3265.866,"stop":3286.971,"duration":21.11},{"text":"Some of the disinterested trustee I have discussed, the others are set forth in our brief.","start":3286.971,"stop":3294.63,"duration":7.66},{"text":"While everyone is anxious to get this case finally over with, this Court through Justice Stone, many years ago in one of the first Chapter X cases, first cases to reach this Court pointed out they're indicated that in Chapter X, the safeguards for public investors are not to be sacrificed for speed and conflict.","start":3294.63,"stop":3318.37,"duration":23.74}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":3318.37,"stop":3326.306,"duration":7.94}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"We have no authority to promulgate a regulation.","start":3326.306,"stop":3329.452,"duration":3.15},{"text":"We did ask Congress several years ago to adopt legislation along this line.","start":3329.452,"stop":3338.929,"duration":9.48},{"text":"I don't even know whether the bill, I think the bill got introduced but it never got to the hearing stage.","start":3338.929,"stop":3344.124,"duration":5.19}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":3344.124,"stop":3345.81,"duration":1.69}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Never got to the hearing stage into the core committee.","start":3345.81,"stop":3350.401,"duration":4.59},{"text":"It sort of, I think believe it died shortly after it was introduced and we've never reintroduced it.","start":3350.401,"stop":3356.699,"duration":6.3}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"What would that bill have provided?","start":3356.699,"stop":3358.52,"duration":1.82}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"That bill would have provided that -- would have put a two year period after the conclusion of reorganization before a trustee of the reorganization could be a President or I believe any other executive officer of a corporation.","start":3358.52,"stop":3374.287,"duration":15.77}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":3374.287,"stop":3380.309,"duration":6.02}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"With this, the rule that we are asking this Court to adopt here is really that no plan can be confirmed where it is proposed that the trustee will be president of the new company and it comes up on the conformation.","start":3380.309,"stop":3397.025,"duration":16.72},{"text":"Now, if this Court were to lay down such a rule and then let's say the initial, the Board of Directors held a meeting three weeks later and threw out the President and elected a new President, I think we would say that was probably the fraud on the Court and that it would appear on the phase of it to be absent, very exceptional circumstances such as that the interim trustee had died or control have changed hands or something of that sort but I think the court would have to work it out, the courts would have to work it out on a case-by-case basis.","start":3397.025,"stop":3434.835,"duration":37.81}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Could I ask you, let's assume to the moment that the Court agreed that you want the contesting President [Inaudible] and agreed with the plan I believe outside of the conformation that [Inaudible]","start":3434.835,"stop":3457.547,"duration":22.71}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"I think that we certainly think if we, if you agree with us I think you would also consistently agree that the plan hearings must be re-had and these compromises --","start":3457.547,"stop":3471.117,"duration":13.57}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":3471.117,"stop":3471.536,"duration":0.42}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Because it seems to me that this conflict permeates everything that is going on.","start":3471.536,"stop":3476.707,"duration":5.17},{"text":"How can the trustee who would settles these --","start":3476.707,"stop":3478.796,"duration":2.09}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible] to your argument just a while ago [Inaudible] trying to that there would be settlement and maybe something wrong with the settlement [Inaudible]","start":3478.796,"stop":3497.281,"duration":18.49}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Well perhaps I did not make myself clear.","start":3497.281,"stop":3499.376,"duration":2.1},{"text":"Prospectively at any given point of time certainly before we knew the trustee was contemplating being President.","start":3499.376,"stop":3507.203,"duration":7.83},{"text":"We could show at that time that here is a man who is working toward a particular end of getting himself to be President.","start":3507.203,"stop":3516.432,"duration":9.23}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you think that without you're so called prophylactic rule wouldn't just be cured or satisfied by appointing a new President.","start":3516.432,"stop":3525.778,"duration":9.35}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh No, very much no sir.","start":3525.778,"stop":3528.451,"duration":2.67}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":3528.451,"stop":3546.169,"duration":17.72}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"This maybe what should follow, but not necessarily.","start":3546.169,"stop":3549.592,"duration":3.42},{"text":"If it becomes clear that the trustee cannot become President then at least the conflict that we are complaining about would not be there for future plan hearings and so forth.","start":3549.592,"stop":3560.296,"duration":10.7},{"text":"Now, it is possible of course that by reason of the recriminations and litigation it might be that the committee or the commission might consider a motion to remove him at that time, but I don't think that the issues are necessarily at all the same.","start":3560.296,"stop":3580.988,"duration":20.69}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"But you do argue I suppose that the Court doesn't go along with you know, this trustee's President if the reorganization was never -- the confirmation was nevertheless be set aside under the ground, several other grounds.","start":3580.988,"stop":3594.802,"duration":13.81}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":3594.802,"stop":3595.662,"duration":0.86}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"But the answer, question I asked Mr. Langbein, I gather, my understanding the SEC position that we agree that there should be a prophylactic rule that automatically that means this whole organization has been unscrambled and started over.","start":3595.662,"stop":3612.01,"duration":16.35}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Well it has to go back most of the way, yes.","start":3612.01,"stop":3614.869,"duration":2.86}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"What do you mean most of the way?","start":3614.869,"stop":3615.676,"duration":0.81}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Well I mean --","start":3615.676,"stop":3616.207,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Go all the way.","start":3616.207,"stop":3617.1,"duration":0.89}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"No in many things there has been no argument about, many claimants, no one dispute of them.","start":3617.1,"stop":3623.964,"duration":6.86},{"text":"The essential things that there have been issues are with respect to are; one the valuation of this company, should the stockholders be cut in.","start":3623.964,"stop":3632.925,"duration":8.96},{"text":"Two, the two large compromises of the two major creditors.","start":3632.925,"stop":3638.866,"duration":5.94},{"text":"Three, whether or not the stockholders have a claim based upon the fraud in the sale of their stock.","start":3638.866,"stop":3647.649,"duration":8.78}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Why wouldn't you have to go back have the 166 [Inaudible] because that's the place after that he was first supposed to be President.","start":3647.649,"stop":3656.881,"duration":9.23},{"text":"I would think that its into your, since that's the critical part of the reorganization, because you have to have it done by someone you felt was the President.","start":3656.881,"stop":3664.136,"duration":7.26}]},{"speakerName":"William O. Douglas","textObjs":[{"text":"That's -- on theory say that people running for President do all sorts of [Inaudible]","start":3664.136,"stop":3669.156,"duration":5.02}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"We are sure he had been President with an earlier group, now whether during that --","start":3669.156,"stop":3675.318,"duration":6.16}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well he had been, the first reorganization plan had him as President.","start":3675.318,"stop":3678.4,"duration":3.08}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"Right.","start":3678.4,"stop":3679.099,"duration":0.7}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"And then that was knocked over and he made an investigation under 157.","start":3679.099,"stop":3683.632,"duration":4.53}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right, conceivably he could have at this time given up his idea of being President.","start":3683.632,"stop":3687.28,"duration":3.65}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"I think this would be the very time where you would say obviously you have to.","start":3687.28,"stop":3692.923,"duration":5.64}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"I would think that --","start":3692.923,"stop":3694.873,"duration":1.95}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well this wouldn't be upset if we adopted your basic position again, that the whole thing was unscrambled with.","start":3694.873,"stop":3701.534,"duration":6.66}]},{"speakerName":"David Ferber","textObjs":[{"text":"I certainly would not Your Honor.","start":3701.534,"stop":3708.192,"duration":6.66}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Simmons.","start":3708.192,"stop":3709.958,"duration":1.77}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, other members of the Court, may I please the Court.","start":3709.958,"stop":3717.168,"duration":7.21},{"text":"There are four issues involved in this case, four general areas of issues and I want to divide my time between the four of them, approximately 15 minutes each roughly, leaving Mr. Spitzer to take his part of the argument.","start":3717.168,"stop":3737.586,"duration":20.42},{"text":"Now I'm going to discuss them in this order there is the question of insolvency, is the debtor insolvent, though the stockholders are to be excluded from it.","start":3737.586,"stop":3747.695,"duration":10.11},{"text":"The second issue is about the employment of the trustee.","start":3747.695,"stop":3752.061,"duration":4.37},{"text":"You heard  been discussing that more than anything else here.","start":3752.061,"stop":3755.725,"duration":3.66},{"text":"The third is whether the stockholders should be invited by the Court to file recession claims based on the alleged frauds that took place back before the reorganization began.","start":3755.725,"stop":3769.492,"duration":13.77},{"text":"We haven't had much discussion on that issue yet.","start":3769.492,"stop":3774.184,"duration":4.69},{"text":"And the fourth issue is about the compromises of the claims, and we're talking about two claims, the Merrill-Stevens Claim, which I'll discuss and the Caplan mortgage claim which Mr. Spitzer will discuss because he is their attorney and one of the trustees.","start":3774.184,"stop":3793.085,"duration":18.9},{"text":"And I'm going to take them up one at a time and I would appreciate the Court ask me questions about each one of these four things at the same time, although I have no objection to get operandi in the other, if you want -- if you feel it pertinent.","start":3793.085,"stop":3808.674,"duration":15.59},{"text":"Now about insolvency.","start":3808.674,"stop":3811.408,"duration":2.73},{"text":"There should be no question about this debtor being insolvent.","start":3811.408,"stop":3816.73,"duration":5.32},{"text":"It's the weakest part in the whole case.","start":3816.73,"stop":3819.276,"duration":2.55},{"text":"Let me just give you the facts and before I get into the facts on this, I want the Court to bear in mind that in every one of these issues, if you're going to reverse the Lower Court, you're going to have to take that record that stacks up this high and study those facts and place yourself in a position of that Trial Judge and ask and try to decide whether you would have decided those facts differently.","start":3819.276,"stop":3849.083,"duration":29.81},{"text":"You might have, you might have in some instances, but I doubt it.","start":3849.083,"stop":3853.145,"duration":4.06},{"text":"Judge Cho, judge Amet Cho who had been on the bench a long time and practiced law a long time before he went on the bench, he's retired or aged 70 here about a year or two ago, but still continues to handle a case.","start":3853.145,"stop":3870.3,"duration":17.16}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible] If the Court says these compromises are in fact they are vulnerable because nothing appears in the record, they maybe absolutely not a compromise but there isn't enough [Inaudible]","start":3870.3,"stop":3889.073,"duration":18.77}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I'll get to that when I get there.","start":3889.073,"stop":3890.621,"duration":1.55},{"text":"There's a lot in the record.","start":3890.621,"stop":3892.24,"duration":1.62},{"text":"Your Honor there's plenty in the record.","start":3892.24,"stop":3893.862,"duration":1.62}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm just saying.","start":3893.862,"stop":3894.609,"duration":0.75}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I know.","start":3894.609,"stop":3896.096,"duration":1.49},{"text":"My argument assumes that there's plenty in the record on the facts to sustain the compromises and if you read what I've outlined in my brief in the record on that -- you'll know a lot about the Merrill-Stevens claim and it's objections.","start":3896.096,"stop":3910.451,"duration":14.36},{"text":"You need just about all you need to know to make a decision as to whether a compromise would be acceptable or not.","start":3910.451,"stop":3919.247,"duration":8.8},{"text":"My statement is based upon the fact that there are a lot of facts in the record.","start":3919.247,"stop":3924.902,"duration":5.66},{"text":"Now on the question of insolvency, what does the evidence in fact show?","start":3924.902,"stop":3930.823,"duration":5.92},{"text":"The total claims against this debtor were in were in excess $5,400,000.","start":3930.823,"stop":3937.615,"duration":6.79},{"text":"Of these claims, over 2 million were either preferred claims, like government tax claims and non-tax claims that had preference or they were claims, secured claims, maritime lien claims or mortgage claims like the Caplan mortgage claim.","start":3937.615,"stop":3961.501,"duration":23.89},{"text":"The company operates under the trustee.","start":3961.501,"stop":3968.803,"duration":7.3},{"text":"The company started out and only it was in existence about a couple of years before it went on and it had this idea, it was run by this man named Rad and he had the idea of rolling on, called roll on roll off method of hauling freight, back in 1956.","start":3968.803,"stop":3985.986,"duration":17.18},{"text":"You roll the trailers, the highway trailers on to the vessel and then you roll them off at the other end, overseas and you don't have to have stevedore and it's a lot easier to load and unload and you use the same trucks for a line haul on each end.","start":3985.986,"stop":4001.221,"duration":15.24}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4001.221,"stop":4002.029,"duration":0.81}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir, yes sir.","start":4002.029,"stop":4003.179,"duration":1.15},{"text":"That's the thing.","start":4003.179,"stop":4004.463,"duration":1.28},{"text":"Back in the mid 1950s this was sort of a coming thing, so it caught on.","start":4004.463,"stop":4010.22,"duration":5.76},{"text":"Since the trustee has taken over he has restricted his operations to hauling these trailer ships as we call them between Miami and Puerto Rico and between Jacksonville and Puerto Rico and all they used this business is five old World War II LST converted, the guts were taken out of them and you try and fix them up so you can haul freight and they are hauled by sea going tugs.","start":4010.22,"stop":4041.67,"duration":31.45}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4041.67,"stop":4044.499,"duration":2.83}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The company was organized in 1955 or it maybe it was in the end of 1954 and the reorganization proceedings began in June 1957.","start":4044.499,"stop":4056.241,"duration":11.74},{"text":"They are now in their 11th year.","start":4056.241,"stop":4058.926,"duration":2.68}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4058.926,"stop":4059.701,"duration":0.78}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":4059.701,"stop":4060.119,"duration":0.42},{"text":"A little over two years.","start":4060.119,"stop":4061.041,"duration":0.92}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4061.041,"stop":4066.623,"duration":5.58}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No sir it may be in there but we don't consider it material at this point.","start":4066.623,"stop":4073.856,"duration":7.23},{"text":"A lot has happened since it began.","start":4073.856,"stop":4076.791,"duration":2.93},{"text":"Getting back to the facts with respect to the -- whether it's solvent or insolvent, as against these $5,400,000 in claims of which over 2 million were preferred or secured or claimed to be secured.","start":4076.791,"stop":4095.057,"duration":18.27},{"text":"The valuation hearings held in the spring of 1962 disclosed that the assets of the company were worth less than $2 million, that is the assets being primarily these old World War II LSTs that were being kept -- that they were -- had converted into barges and were running, plus their motor vehicle equipment and shop equipment and terminal equipment was worth less than $2,000.","start":4095.057,"stop":4124.711,"duration":29.65},{"text":"We had valuation proceedings which are rather extensive in the record on the value of these assets.","start":4124.711,"stop":4131.125,"duration":6.41},{"text":"2 million, I'm sorry I made a mistake.","start":4131.125,"stop":4136.073,"duration":4.95},{"text":"But the business had made money under the trustee whereas it had not made money under the former poor management that ran it in the ground, because he was a good successful trustee they made money and ","start":4136.073,"stop":4153.719,"duration":17.65}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4153.719,"stop":4154.627,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No, he had nothing whatever to do with the company in any way, shape, or form before and he met all of those requirements of the statute, he wasn't a stockholder, he wasn't a creditor.","start":4154.627,"stop":4165.895,"duration":11.27},{"text":"He had no interest, he never heard of TMT until the Court appointed him as trustee.","start":4165.895,"stop":4171.359,"duration":5.46},{"text":"So the company had made money under the trusteeship and it's going concern value based on it's earnings under the trusteeship up to that time reflected that it's value was worth more than this $2 million in assets.","start":4171.359,"stop":4187.916,"duration":16.56},{"text":"Our expert that is the trustee's expert on the subject placed the going concern value at $1,800,000.","start":4187.916,"stop":4198.436,"duration":10.52},{"text":"The expert put on the stand by the stockholders committee, placed the going concern value at about $4,000,500.","start":4198.436,"stop":4208.666,"duration":10.23},{"text":"The trustee computed the going-concern value at about $2 million, and the district judge found the going-concern value to be $2,780,000.","start":4208.666,"stop":4222.8,"duration":14.13},{"text":"This was based on the then high earnings of the company that is the estimated earnings for the year 1962 capitalized, is the way the court found that value.","start":4222.8,"stop":4236.984,"duration":14.18},{"text":"The earnings during the seven years of the trusteeship that are that the -- firm figures are in the record that is for the years 1958 to 1964 varied, the net earnings varied from $200,000 per year to $524,000.","start":4236.984,"stop":4258.657,"duration":21.67},{"text":"They have been less in recent years.","start":4258.657,"stop":4261.344,"duration":2.69},{"text":"They've had --","start":4261.344,"stop":4262.44,"duration":1.1}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4262.44,"stop":4263.764,"duration":1.32}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That is -- this is in the record, these are -- financial statements are in the record certified by that certified public account as to the earnings of the company.","start":4263.764,"stop":4278.315,"duration":14.55},{"text":"The court accepting these financial statements as accurate made of finding of going-concern value.","start":4278.315,"stop":4288.334,"duration":10.02},{"text":"Now in determining whether, bear in mind that the issue is not what is the going-concern value of the debtor, the issue is the debtor solvent or not.","start":4288.334,"stop":4301.181,"duration":12.85},{"text":"So this going-concern value does not have to be fixed and determined accurately, as you would in a condemnation suit or possibly a rate base in a rate case.","start":4301.181,"stop":4312.517,"duration":11.34},{"text":"The only reason for computing the going-concern value is to determine whether or not the debtor is solvent.","start":4312.517,"stop":4319.191,"duration":6.67},{"text":"In this case it's important because of the success of the trustee; the going-concern value is more than the cash value or the value of the assets from sales.","start":4319.191,"stop":4333.166,"duration":13.98},{"text":"The district judge found it to be, he found it to be $2,780,000.","start":4333.166,"stop":4339.571,"duration":6.4}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4339.571,"stop":4349.264,"duration":9.69}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The value that you would pay for this business as a going-concern and it is computed by capitalizing the estimated earnings of the business, not its sale value of its assets.","start":4349.264,"stop":4365.648,"duration":16.38}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4365.648,"stop":4369.989,"duration":4.34}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Not the sale or cash value of its assets, no.","start":4369.989,"stop":4374.814,"duration":4.83}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4374.814,"stop":4378.464,"duration":3.65}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"By going-concern value we mean what is its value as a going business earning money.","start":4378.464,"stop":4384.93,"duration":6.47},{"text":"Earning money and it's based on the capitalization of the earnings.","start":4384.93,"stop":4388.616,"duration":3.69}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4388.616,"stop":4401.117,"duration":12.5}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Going-concern value is computed on profits, on the earnings of the business.","start":4401.117,"stop":4406.241,"duration":5.12}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4406.241,"stop":4407.765,"duration":1.52}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"As distinguished from the value of the physical assets itself.","start":4407.765,"stop":4414.353,"duration":6.59},{"text":"Now the only criticism, the SEC admits that it appears that from these figures that I have given you this, this debtor is hopelessly insolvent and I want to -- before I get to their point, I want to point this out that the $5,400,000 figure of the total value of the claims is not the figure that you have to use to determine solvency or not.","start":4414.353,"stop":4440.215,"duration":25.86},{"text":"Interest must be paid to creditors on their claims before stockholders can get anything if the company is solvent and the courts have so held.","start":4440.215,"stop":4451.929,"duration":11.71},{"text":"So we are not talking about in this case $5,400,000 in claims, but through the years the interest on these claims would make the insolvency even greater than it would appear from the figures that I have given.","start":4451.929,"stop":4466.853,"duration":14.92},{"text":"Now the only real issue in this point is did the district court fail to consider evidence of probable growth of the business after reorganization.","start":4466.853,"stop":4478.938,"duration":12.09},{"text":"The SEC's contention is that the law requires recognition of contemplated changes in operations and acquisitions that are likely to take place after reorganization.","start":4478.938,"stop":4495.732,"duration":16.79},{"text":"They are indicated in this case that those changes will have to take place.","start":4495.732,"stop":4500.987,"duration":5.26},{"text":"These changes will have to take place because these old LSTs have got to be replaced.","start":4500.987,"stop":4507.185,"duration":6.2},{"text":"They were expendable.","start":4507.185,"stop":4509.541,"duration":2.36},{"text":"They were built 22 years ago, and they were designed to be destroyed quickly and they don't have thick skins and this company spends tremendous sums of money every year to the Coast Guard, makes them bring them in, replate them and they just spend hundreds of thousands of dollars every year and it's in the record, keeping these old LSTs running, they've got to be replaced by more modern barges.","start":4509.541,"stop":4534.281,"duration":24.74},{"text":"So naturally the trustee is looking and thinking about replacing them and what's going to be the cost.","start":4534.281,"stop":4542.379,"duration":8.1},{"text":"It is going to cost from $1 million to $2 million to build another type vessel that will be efficient and you got to have, you got to replace all five of them.","start":4542.379,"stop":4552.925,"duration":10.55},{"text":"But that's as far as the trustee can go.","start":4552.925,"stop":4556.074,"duration":3.15},{"text":"He can't commit in his planning the reorganized company what it's going to do to replace these vessels.","start":4556.074,"stop":4563.55,"duration":7.48},{"text":"He can't determine the financing of this thing.","start":4563.55,"stop":4566.958,"duration":3.41},{"text":"In fact the SEC even says, he shouldn't even be thinking about it and yet in their argument they say that the trustee should have brought in to the court an estimate of going-concern value based on prospective earnings in the future, based on new vessels and new financing of those vessels in the future.","start":4566.958,"stop":4588.269,"duration":21.31},{"text":"Now the trial court after hearing all this evidence on this subject, and we did have two experts that looked into the future and gave their opinion, the trial court said all this speculation about future profits and earnings on the change conditions with new vessels and new kind of financing is not reliable.","start":4588.269,"stop":4606.171,"duration":17.9},{"text":"The most reliable information is that which we have of the trustees' own operations and everything is in this record concerning what has been done under all the years of the trustees operations up to the time the two evaluation hearings were held and bear in mind that this plan has been through the mail twice.","start":4606.171,"stop":4628.306,"duration":22.13},{"text":"It went through the mail once in 1962, it went up to the Appellate Court and came back and the same plan has been through the mail again.","start":4628.306,"stop":4637.958,"duration":9.65},{"text":"So we've had two evaluation hearings, one in 1962 and another one in 1965 and the trustees  and the Court found that the company in 1965 had not been making as much money as it had before the previous evaluation hearings and so it said that if it had to make another finding of going concern value it would be less now than it was at that time.","start":4637.958,"stop":4667.416,"duration":29.46}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"What percentage of their claims were the unsecured creditors?","start":4667.416,"stop":4672.906,"duration":5.49}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The unsecured creditors had originally about three 3,200,000 and the preferred and secured 2,200,000.","start":4672.906,"stop":4685.375,"duration":12.47}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"So the preferred claims just about to took the all the value?","start":4685.375,"stop":4689.507,"duration":4.13}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":4689.507,"stop":4690.697,"duration":1.19},{"text":"Now we converted -- one of the compromises was to convert $5,574,000 of the alleged secured claims of Merrill-Stevens over in to the unsecured class, that was the compromise and reduce it.","start":4690.697,"stop":4708.421,"duration":17.72}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"And what percentage of the unsecured creditors claim was actually recognized in a way of stock, I suppose they got stock didn't they?","start":4708.421,"stop":4719.724,"duration":11.3}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"All of he unsecured creditors, got all of the stock in the new company.","start":4719.724,"stop":4726.504,"duration":6.78}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"And the preferred claims [Inaudible]","start":4726.504,"stop":4728.786,"duration":2.28}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"They didn't get any, now since you've asked the question, Your Honor.","start":4728.786,"stop":4731.848,"duration":3.06}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4731.848,"stop":4734.009,"duration":2.16}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I'll go into that now because it's important.","start":4734.009,"stop":4736.305,"duration":2.3},{"text":"This is the simplest most equitable plan of reorganization you can think of.","start":4736.305,"stop":4741.835,"duration":5.53},{"text":"I can't think of a simpler one.","start":4741.835,"stop":4743.936,"duration":2.1},{"text":"I've outlined the situation with respect to the claims.","start":4743.936,"stop":4747.986,"duration":4.05},{"text":"In the plan of reorganization since debtor is obviously insolvent, all the new common stock is given the unsecured or common creditors in proportion to their claims, when we got through converting some of them to -- in compromising some of them over to unsecured they total about three million, seven or eight thousand dollars.","start":4747.986,"stop":4770.644,"duration":22.66},{"text":"So the company is turned over to its unsecured creditors and they swap their claims for the common stock prorata and the secured creditors and the preferred creditors are all paid all in cash and Your Honors they have been paid off in cash.","start":4770.644,"stop":4790.972,"duration":20.33},{"text":"They have been paid off in cash.","start":4790.972,"stop":4794.882,"duration":3.91},{"text":"This plan has been consummated substantially.","start":4794.882,"stop":4798.613,"duration":3.73},{"text":"All the preferred creditors and all the secured creditors have been paid.","start":4798.613,"stop":4805.348,"duration":6.73}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Was the Merrill claim, a maritime name case?","start":4805.348,"stop":4809.09,"duration":3.74}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"$574,000 of it was and it's compromise was to convert it to unsecured and it has been paid in stock.","start":4809.09,"stop":4818.226,"duration":9.14}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Otherwise Merrill's claim was just an unsecured claim?","start":4818.226,"stop":4821.068,"duration":2.84}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir, out of the $1,600,000 claim, roughly 1 million of it was unsecured from the beginning and nearly 600,000 was preferred.","start":4821.068,"stop":4831.057,"duration":9.99}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible] mortgage claims that are that were also settled they were paid in cash?","start":4831.057,"stop":4835.229,"duration":4.17}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The capital and mortgage claim of 330,000 plus interest, costs, attorneys fees and everything was settled for $250,000 in cash and the 250,000 has been paid to it.","start":4835.229,"stop":4850.046,"duration":14.82},{"text":"That's the plan, it's a simpler plan as you can think of and that is the plan that they were trying to sustain here, to turn this company over its common creditor yes Your Honor.","start":4850.046,"stop":4860.603,"duration":10.56}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible","start":4860.603,"stop":4862.965,"duration":2.36}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"No sir, the company is insolvent so they have no equity in it and no right to participate and since the company is hopelessly insolvent under the facts in this case.","start":4862.965,"stop":4872.948,"duration":9.98}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Unless they are -- unless they have a claim that the company could not recognized?","start":4872.948,"stop":4877.861,"duration":4.91}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That's another issue, that's an entirely different issue.","start":4877.861,"stop":4880.417,"duration":2.56}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4880.417,"stop":4885.145,"duration":4.73}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"A little over two years, two and a half years at the most.","start":4885.145,"stop":4890.539,"duration":5.39}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4890.539,"stop":4891.385,"duration":0.85}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes Your Honor rather, rather amazing.","start":4891.385,"stop":4894.164,"duration":2.78}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4894.164,"stop":4896.019,"duration":1.86}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes it had it had a lot of stockholders.","start":4896.019,"stop":4898.513,"duration":2.49},{"text":"At the time the reorganization proceeding began there were a lot of stockholders that bought the stock on the open market.","start":4898.513,"stop":4904.818,"duration":6.31}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4904.818,"stop":4908.209,"duration":3.39}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"It was -- most of it was issued to persons in payment for services and materials and supplies and equipment and that sort of thing and some of it was issued for cash and sold, very little of it was registered.","start":4908.209,"stop":4923.674,"duration":15.47}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":4923.674,"stop":4925.869,"duration":2.19}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right very little of it.","start":4925.869,"stop":4934.14,"duration":8.27},{"text":"Getting into the -- so closing out the -- on the issue of insolvency I think there is plenty of evidence in the record to show this debtor is insolvent and I don't see how the Court find otherwise.","start":4934.14,"stop":4945.995,"duration":11.85}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the claims against outsider with the trustees just existed at one point, did those claims against outside [Inaudible] compromises that were approved?","start":4945.995,"stop":4955.967,"duration":9.97}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Only some of them, when I come to discussing the compromises --","start":4955.967,"stop":4959.044,"duration":3.08}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"So that would certainly increase the assets of the company, if those claims were good and they were collected?","start":4959.044,"stop":4965.343,"duration":6.3}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"They weren't though, we decided that they -- we pursued some of it, we pursued we filed two suits --","start":4965.343,"stop":4972.623,"duration":7.28}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Claim to extent the claim to extent that the claim is made here that trustee did not pursuit claims that should have been pursued, if the trustee should have pursued then he would have collected the money.","start":4972.623,"stop":4985.483,"duration":12.86}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":4985.483,"stop":4986.085,"duration":0.6}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"There would have some more assets to the company.","start":4986.085,"stop":4988.14,"duration":2.06}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The principal ones they are complaining about are the counter claims against the claims of Merrill-Stevens and the captain mortgage.","start":4988.14,"stop":4996.907,"duration":8.77}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"And those claims you say wash out with the company?","start":4996.907,"stop":5000.339,"duration":3.43}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right I do.","start":5000.339,"stop":5003.242,"duration":2.9},{"text":"One more point on that insolvency, if you wiped out -- Your Honor if you wiped out those claims entirely, you wiped out those two claims entirely nearly $2,000,000 worth, the company would still be insolvent.","start":5003.242,"stop":5018.242,"duration":15},{"text":"The fact of insolvency is the most important fact here because these stockholders have got no right to complaint against the compromise of these claims, because they have no equity in them, the compromise is of concern only to the creditors.","start":5018.242,"stop":5032.063,"duration":13.82}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"[Inaudible]","start":5032.063,"stop":5040.274,"duration":8.21}]},{"speakerName":"William P. Simmons, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think -- it is my opinion Your Honor that if you took every favorable factor that they have, I still don't believe it would be solvent because you'd have to add interest to those claims and if you took their experts most favorable one, I don't think it would be solvent, I'll go into the rest of it tomorrow.","start":5040.274,"stop":5068.487,"duration":28.21}]}]}],"decidedBy":"Warren Court","arguedOn":"Nov  7 - 8, 1967","petitioner":"Protective Committee for Independent Stockholders of TMT Trailer Ferry, Inc.","respondent":"Anderson","docket":"38","citation":"390US414(1968)","justiaLink":"https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/390/414","lowerCourt":"United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit","grantedOn":"","decidedOn":"Mar 25, 1968"}